title: smokey beans
directions: Brown burger and drain.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until warmed through or place in oven and heat for 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: diann's fudge brownies
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sugar, then stir in plain flour.
Mix well and pour into pan that is greased or sprayed with Pam (7 x 12-inch Pyrex dish).
Cook at 350°.
Be careful not to overcook.
Delicious!

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook celery in butter until soft.
Mix chicken and bread crumbs in bowl.
Add cooked celery and mix lightly.
Stir milk into flour, onion and seasonings.
Place in a 1-quart glass casserole.
Add crushed bouillon cube.
Cook with microwave and let come to a boil, stirring every 30 seconds.
Place chicken and crumb mixture in 1 1/2-quart glass utility dish.
Pour hot milk mixture over chicken and top with buttered crumbs.
Cover and cook 6 to 7 minutes.
If desired, use glass ceramic dish to cook and place under the broiler or conventional range to brown the top.

title: coconut blender pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a blender, combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla.	Blend on low 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut.	Pour into greased 9 inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak fingers
directions: Put steak into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Salt and pepper to taste. Beat egg and milk together.
Dip steak in flour, then into egg mixture.
Then press steak in cracker meal to coat.
Fry in large skillet in hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Serves 4.

title: blt dip
directions: Fry bacon & crumble.
Mix sour cream & mayo, add crumbled bacon, then add chopped tomato.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt & pepper.
Stir (may have to add more mayo).
Let set overnight before serving.

title: avocado sauce
directions: Spread bean dip, then avocado.
Sprinkle with tomatoes, onions, olives, then Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken and crab meat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften butter and cheese spread to room temperature.
Add mayonnaise, garlic salt and seasoned salt; blend thoroughly.
Add crab meat.
Spread on split muffins.
If for immediate use, freeze on cookie sheet for 10 minutes, thaw.
Cut into eighths.
Broil until bubbly.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix dry mustard and apple jelly thoroughly first.
Add prepared horseradish, pineapple preserves and cracked peppercorns. Makes 3 2/3 cups.
Serve over cream cheese and with crackers of choice.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Add buttermilk; stir just until dough clings together.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add the oil, apples and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Fold into mixture and mix thoroughly; stir in nuts and dates.
Bake in 10-inch greased tube or loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: wynn's s'mores bars
directions: Arrange graham crackers in a single layer in a greased 13x9 in. pan.
Prepare the brownie batter according to package.
Spread over crackers. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and peanuts.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until marshmallows are slightly puffed and golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack before cutting.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes and rest of ingredients.
Beat to blend.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix egg, milk, salt and sugar.
Add flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Bake in hot, greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, or small skillet, at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices. Line foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate; carefully remove foil.
Invert to right side.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine for 3 minutes.
Remove onion from pan.
Saute hamburger until golden brown.
Boil macaroni 20 minutes in water with 2 teaspoons salt.
Drain macaroni and combine with hamburger.
Add onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper, garlic powder and Accent.
Fold in corn. Place mixture in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with pie filling before serving.

title: southern lemon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, well beaten.
Stir in lemon extract.
Mix together sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk.
Fold in 4 well beaten egg whites.
Bake in well greased layer cake pans. Bake in a moderately hot oven for about 25 minutes.

title: homestyle pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Shake flour in Reynolds Oven Bag; place in 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking pan.
Add water and onion soup mix to oven bag.
Squeeze bag to blend in flour.
Add beef to bag. Turn bag to coat beef with sauce.
Place potatoes, onion and carrots in bag around beef.
Close oven bag with nylon tie, cut six 1/2 inch slits in top.
Tuck ends of bag in pan.
Bake 2 hours until meat thermometer reads 160 degrees.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving, if desired.

title: casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion; drain good.
Stir in the soup, spaghetti and vegetables all together.
Put in an ungreased baking dish, about 11 x 7-inches.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until it is bubbly.
When taken out of oven, sprinkle with cheese and let stand for a few minutes until melted.

title: ala tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles 10 to 12 minutes; let stand.
Salt and pepper noodles to taste.
Warm soup and milk together until smooth texture is formed.
Open tuna.
Layer noodles, tuna, cheese and soup in amounts to cover casserole dish.
Repeat until all are used up, usually 2 to 3 layers.
Bake in the oven at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and serve.
Good with salad and biscuits.

title: finger licking' good cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan.

In a large mixing bowl, mix the cake mix, oranges with juice, melted butter, oil, eggs and pineapple juice. Blend on low speed for 1 minute. Scrape down sides and mix on medium speed for 2 more minutes.
Pour mixture into prepared pan and bake for 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Frost.

title: fantastic strawberry jello with sour cream
directions: You can use a 9 x 12-inch oblong Pyrex dish.

title: peanut butter monsters - chewy(cookies)
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream margarine.
Add sugars and beat until light.
Add eggs and beat again.
Then add syrup, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Sprinkle the soda over dry oatmeal and blend into mix.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: very old fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly; boil until soft to medium-ball stage. Add vanilla and beat with a wooden spoon until stiff. Add nuts, if desired. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and let set.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and parsley. Slice potatoes in casserole dish, sprinkle on onion.
Top with sauce. Put browned pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Place heavy-duty aluminum foil in baking pan and place roast on foil.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat and spread mushroom soup. Fold foil securely over roast and bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to cream.
Stir.
Mix pumpkin, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pour in ice cube tray and freeze until firm.
Remove to bowl and beat until free of lumps.
Fill crust; finish freezing.

title: cheezy broccoli
directions: Place unopened packages of broccoli on end in microwave and microwave on High, 4 to 5 minutes.
Set aside to thaw.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine rice, soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High, 2 to 4 minutes until cheese melts and can be blended easily.
To cheese mixture, add onions, celery, water chestnuts and broccoli.
Stir thoroughly.
Divide evenly between 2 lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dishes.
Microwave one dish at a time.
Microwave on High, 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Beat butter with sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, pineapple, and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix then fold in nuts.
Bake in bundt pan.
Cool in bundt pan for 10 minutes then turn out. Frost.

title: microwave orange glazed carrots
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine juice, honey, butter, orange peel, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in cornstarch; mix until well blended.
Stir in carrots.
Cover with lid.
Cook at High for 8 to 10 minutes; stir once.
Stir; let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine and press into bottom of 9-inch pie pan.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies(from an old oatmeal box)
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix. Add flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Mix. Add water, oats, chocolate chips and nuts.

title: maui potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle mushrooms over potatoes.
Sprinkle green onions over mushrooms.
In saucepan melt margarine, soup, sour cream and cheese. Pour over potatoes and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jumbo shells with cheese stuffing(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Cook jumbo shells as directed.
Drain and dry in a single layer on paper towel.
Combine cheese with beaten eggs, salt, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Fill the shells with 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift together.
Add beaten egg, buttermilk and chopped onion and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot fat and cook to a golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
Yields 12 to 16 hush puppies.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper and coat both sides with cornmeal.
In large skillet, heat enough Crisco to coat bottom of pan.
Fry tomatoes until lightly browned on both sides.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In one bowl, mix powdered sugar and crushed vanilla wafers. In saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter.
In bowl, mix both the wet and dry ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Chill.

title: old fashion fruit cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients well.
Then add last 4 ingredients. Line 2 large loaf pans or 1 large tube pan with foil and grease. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Let cool completely.
Serves 12.

title: tortilla vegetable roll-ups
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate 2 hours.
Heat 8-inch tortillas in microwave on High 5 to 10 seconds to soften.
Spread each with 1 to 2 tablespoons mixture and roll up jelly roll style. Cut in slices to serve.

title: ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Remove from pan.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: turnovers
directions: Cut lard and flour until crumbly. Add salt, milk and eggs. Chill overnight.
Roll out in powdered sugar.
Add fruit.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: rocky road dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, melted margarine and 1/2 cup pecans. Press in bottom of baking pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.

title: broccoli and macaroni
directions: In frypan, saute oil, chopped garlic and partly cooked broccoli (or frozen).
Simmer with lid on for 15 to 20 minutes. Add to cooked macaroni.
Sprinkle with lots of cheese.
Serve with warm Italian bread and eat hearty!

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cool slightly.
In mixer or food processor, puree all ingredients except chocolate and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add melted chocolate.
Blend well.
Pour into lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
After baking, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into 16 squares.
Calories:
107 per serving; 3 grams fat.

title: mihshe malfuf(stuffed cabbage leaves)
directions: Core and parboil cabbage until limp and easy to roll.
Place in colander and separate leaves.
Slice each leaf in half on rib. Leaves should be 4 inches long to 6 inches wide (keep uniform). Mix rice, meat and spices.
Place 1 tablespoon on each leaf. Spread lengthwise along rib and roll up.
Gently squeeze each roll when placing in pan.
Arrange in compact layers.
Dice 3 cloves of garlic and sprinkle between each layer.
Mash 1 clove garlic with mint and salt and add lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly and pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover cabbage with water, 1/2 inch above top layer.
Place a pottery plate over rolls to keep them firm and intact.
Cover pan and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until rice is done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: double chocolate cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fold in chocolate morsels.
Spoon into foil or paper-lined muffin pans, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans immediately; cool on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yield:
1 dozen (about 153 calories each). Protein. 2.3.
Fat 5.5
Carb.
Choles. 0.
Iron 0.9. Sodium 167.
Calcium 23.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Cook on low heat the chocolate bar, marshmallows and milk stirring continually until smooth. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours. Decorate with candy bar pieces or shavings.

title: hungarian goulash(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Coat steak and onion with flour and pepper; put steak, onion, tomatoes and mushrooms in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
In last 1/2 hour, add sour cream and stir.
Serve with Kluski noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift flour and 10x sugar together.
Cut butter into flour and 10x sugar until mixture clings together.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until lightly browned).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Peel and slice potatoes and layer in casserole.
Peel and slice onions.
Layer on top of potatoes.
Layer more potatoes over onions.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Dot with pats of butter sparingly.
Dilute soup with milk and pour over vegetables.
Brown pork chops and place on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes and chops are done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown onion and beef in a skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
While stuffing is simmering, cut pepper tops off and clean seeds out.
Stuff peppers and put a spoonful of tomato sauce on top of each.
Place peppers on grill. Cover and cook 40 to 50 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water and add V-8 juice.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Serves 9.

title: foolproof popovers
directions: You will need 6 cold, greased custard cups.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together well (I mix with mixer).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 17 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: coconut ball cookies
directions: Mix well and shape into small balls, then roll in coconut.

title: oriental salad
directions: Break up the noodles and mix with the next 4 ingredients. Make a dressing of the oil, sugar, vinegar and 2 packets of flavoring from the Ramen noodles. Mix
and chill for 1 hour. Add dressing to slaw mixture just before serving.

title: grilled grouper or amberjack
directions: Marinate grouper or amberjack overnight in mixture of all ingredients, except butter and green onions.
Spray grill with nonstick coating.
Place grouper or amberjack directly on hot grill.
Cook for about 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Take up on warmed platter; pour melted butter and green onions over top. Serve immediately.

title: monkey bread
directions: Let bread rise completely in well-greased pan.
Turn out on floured surface and cut in cubes the size of a plum.
Roll each piece in melted oleo, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Pile back in pan; let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Pull apart to eat.

title: large fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit juices.
Mix fruit with Cool Whip, raisins or nuts and marshmallows.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over when Cool Whip is added.
If this is dry, spoon in a few spoons of fruit juice.
Large salad, is good to make a few days ahead of time.

title: congealed pretzel salad
directions: Cream margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in pretzels.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet; add spices and stir well.
Add sugar and pecans; cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted, approximately 8 minutes.
Pour out on flat buttered pan to cool, separating nuts.

title: mornay sauce (france)
directions: * Recipe in this book.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well in this order: shortening, sugar, eggs, flavoring, flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Chill at least 1 hour. Roll to 1/8-inch
on
floured
board.
Cut
with 3-inch cookie cutter. Place
on ungreased baking sheet.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked chicken and broccoli curry
directions: Place cooked broccoli in greased baking dish. Place chicken on top of broccoli. Mix soup, milk, mayo, lemon juice and curry. Pour over broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture and top with buttered bread crumbs. (Can substitute crushed croutons for bread crumbs and margarine.) Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: brandied yam bake
directions: Drain the pineapple and set aside.
Cut the yams into chunks. Melt the butter in a large skillet and add the brown sugar, brandy, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cook on high heat 3-4 minutes to reduce liquid to a syrup.
Add the yams and cook until glazed. Spoon into a 3-qt. casserole and arrange the pineapple and walnuts on the top.
Pour any remaining syrup over the top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 4-6 servings.

title: apple butter crock-pot
directions: Fill crock-pot to top with diced apples.
Turn on low; cook 12 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Turn on high.
Cook 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Add chicken. Mix together chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Sprinkle soft bread crumbs over all. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: strawberry crunch cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar till light and fluffy. Add 2 eggs; beat well. Blend in sour cream.

title: almond butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Finely grind almonds and 1/4 cup sugar in processor.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add butter and cut in using on/off turns until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yolk and extract, blend until dough forms clumps.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on prepared cookie sheet, spacing evenly. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: six can casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in a greased casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: chicken & rice
directions: Mix rice and seasoning packet together with the 6 cans of soup.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Spread in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Lay chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of chicken breasts.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350 degrees. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: onion spoon bread
directions: Saute onions in 2 teaspoons butter. Beat the egg and milk together and add the corn bread mix. Fold in the onions and 1/2 cup of the cheese. Pour batter into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Top with the poppy seeds, the 3 tablespoons of additional butter and the remaining cheese. DON'T COVER THE CASSEROLE! Bake for 25 minutes at 400°

title: hot spiced wine
directions: Combine water, sugar, lemon slices and orange slices in a Dutch oven; tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to sugar mixture and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard spice bag; serve hot.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill and serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Cook onion in oleo until tender. Combine meat, crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and seasoning. Beat till fluffy with mixer, about 5 minutes.
Form into balls and brown in oleo.
Remove meatballs.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix per package directions. Set aside. Combine Ranch dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise and set aside. Combine tomatoes, green pepper and onions and set aside. Reserve some crumbled bacon for garnish.

title: the basic i-hate-to-cook muffin
directions: Mix it so it's barely a batter but no more; don't beat it. Pour into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: country boy's best deer bologna
directions: Grind
meat once.
Place meat into wooden tub.	Add all dry ingredients;
mix well.
Add syrup and liquid smoke.
Mix well. Grind
again.
Stuff
meat	into
casings and tie shut. Bake 5 hours in 200° oven and turn every 1/2 hour.
Or bake 3 hours in 225°oven and turn every 1/2 hour.
Bologna is not as dry at
225°. Casings
can
be made from old material to size desired.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, add vinegar and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Dissolve orange jello in hot water.
Add plain gelatine in cold water.
When all is cool, add crushed pineapple and grated carrots. (I always add plain gelatine so salad will be firm.)
Put in refrigerator until firmly set.

title: grandma's raisins filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg, sour milk, soda and vanilla to flavor.
Add enough flour to roll thin.

title: italian walnut cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt in separate bowl.
Alternate, adding flour mixture and buttermilk to sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 cups coconut and 1 cup nuts.
Add eggs whites and mix well.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili con cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour chili into ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour batter over chili.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground chuck in 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Continue cooking until done.
Drain fat from ground chuck and set aside.

title: key lime pie(or lemon pie)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked chicken in a long Pyrex dish.
Place cooked broccoli on top.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Place can of onion rings on top of casserole.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix them thoroughly and add tears of joy and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love and kindly service. Fold in 4 cups of prayers and faith to lighten ingredients and raise the texture of great height of Christian living.

title: individual taco salads
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Brown the ground beef; drain and add to macaroni.
Stir in salsa and taco sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine with tortilla chips, lettuce and cheese.
Top with sour cream and serve.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and refried beans.
In baking dish, layer chips, beef mixture and beans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix in order.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry, drain and crumble bacon.
Set aside.
Heat 3 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms, rice and soy sauce.
Cook 10 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beaten egg and cook only until egg is done.
Add bacon and mix well.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Mix cereals, pretzels and nuts in a large roasting pan.
In small saucepan melt butter and add seasonings and Worcestershire.
Pour over snack mix and stir gently from bottom with large fork until coated.
Bake 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup. Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until creamy.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Beat until fluffy.
Layer bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding mixture.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil for about 25 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce on potatoes. Cook, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: prune bars
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped prunes and let cool.
When cool, stir soda into prunes and stir.
Mix all ingredients well. Pour into pan that has been sprayed.
I prefer square pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Each bar counts as 1 bread, 1 fruit and 1/2 milk.

title: gran's noodles
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Add egg in center of flour.
Also add water equal to 1/2 of 1/2 an eggshell.
Mix well (using plenty of flour).
Roll on floured board until very thin.
Roll dough into cylinder and cut thin.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, beating until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla, beating until light and fluffy.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk; cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 cups oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let set 1/2 hour.

title: poppy seed spread for ham biscuits
directions: Mix all and spread on rolls.
Use ham and Swiss cheese.
Heat in oven before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Put in oblong dish. Crumble chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno cheese squares(hot!  sometimes known as "texas fudge")
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in ungreased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chilled cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumber and let stand for 30 minutes; drain. Combine rest of ingredients. Toss in cucumbers. Chill at least 30 minutes. Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter and cookie crumbs and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high speed for about 4 minutes. Add powdered sugar, 3/4 cup butter and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes. Spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes.
Drain pineapple and spread over creamed mixture.
Arrange bananas over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with pecans and garnish with cherries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Better yet when made 2 days ahead.
Serves 12.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir and boil sugar, milk and cocoa for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet to cook and set.

title: coconut pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, pumpkin and coconut. Bake in unbaked pie shell for 55 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 pies.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
Melt butter and add the brown sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 30 seconds or until well blended.
Cool and add the egg.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt to the mix.
Stir in the vanilla and walnuts.
Then spread them in the pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Put crescent rolls in pie pan to form a crust.
Brown ground meat.
Add chili seasoning mix, 1/2 cup water and sliced olives. Simmer a few minutes.
Put into pie plate.
Top with sour cream and then grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: slovenske kolacky
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup of milk.
In mixing bowl, sift flour, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and yeast mixture and butter.
Knead well until dough is smooth.
Set aside 2 1/2 hours to rise.
Turn out on lightly floured board and let rest for 1/2 hour.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares; fill with nut, poppy seed, prune or apricot filling.
Gather up two corners carefully, folding one over the other.
Pinch together.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a new 8 ounce 9-inch pot.

title: oven baked spaghetti
directions: Grease four individual ovenproof dishes and place a quarter of the spaghetti in each one.
Pour tomatoes over the top.
Add the onion; sprinkle with oregano and season well.
Arrange the sliced cheese over the top of the spaghetti mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: panocha icing
directions: Melt margarine. Stir in brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring all the time. Add sweet milk or cream.
Let boil up all over; set off to cool. Beat in powdered sugar or thickness desired, then ice the cake.

title: venison chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until colored.
Add venison and rest of ingredients.
Blend.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add more beer if it gets too dry.
Cook until it is well thickened and rich in flavor.
Serve with pinto or kidney beans and rice.

title: scrumptious chicken vegetable stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large, microwave-safe bowl. Stir to combine. Cover; microwave on High power about 25 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are done. Add more broth, if needed. Garnish with parsley. Serves 6.

title: chicken-tel casserole
directions: Boil hen
in
plenty of water until tender.
Save water to cook
spaghetti
in.
Boil onion and pepper in butter until done. Remove
hen
from
bones and chop.	Combine cooked spaghetti, chicken
and remainder of ingredients, cutting cheese into cubes and
mixing
well.	Bake
at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
This freezes well.
Makes a lot.

title: morning glory margarita
directions: Process the lime juice, tequila, liqueur and ice cubes in a blender until smooth.
Pour into a wine glass, with a salted rim, if desired, and garnish with a morning glory.
Makes 1 drink.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Use small packages of cheese*.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Line dish with crushed cracker crumbs reserving 2 tablespoons. Add the cooked onions and mushroom soup in layers.
Beat the eggs with milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then pour over the casserole.
Sprinkle cheese and the reserved cracker crumbs over the top of the casserole and bake until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat until fluffy, then fold in pineapple and bread.
Place in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be doubled for a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Great with ham or bacon and sausage.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 5 minutes in preheated 350° oven. Top with Eagle Brand milk and coconut. Bake 15 minutes longer. Set aside and melt large Hershey bar on top. Use back of spoon to spread melted chocolate on top and cool. Yields 10 to 12.

title: healthful brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine the next 4 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Blend the 2 mixtures together.
Spread batter in 8 x 8-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16 bars.
Serves 16.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls side by side on a cookie sheet.
Press lines together. Bake as directed. Cool crust. Mix cream cheese with dressing; spread on crust. Cut vegetables; press on pizza, then sprinkle with grated cheese and refrigerate.

title: tv snack
directions: Mix and bake at 250 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour hot water over bran and set aside to cool.
Mix together other ingredients.
Add cooled bran mix.
Don't overbeat.
Bake in muffin cups 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares after cooled.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl. Beat eggs in a medium-size bowl.
Mix in milk and melted butter. Stir into dry ingredients just until blended.
Makes about 8 pancakes.

title: aunt annie's relish pickles
directions: Grind cukes, peppers and onions.
Add 1 quart water; boil for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, seed and turmeric. Cook for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Gently add strawberries.
Place in pie crust.
Stir together remaining 1/2 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar in a small bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of pie. Wrap edges of pie with foil.
Bake at 400° in the center of the oven rack for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix as listed and put in fridge until ready to serve and it is jelled good.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Mix and beat well.
Add more flour, if needed.
Store in large mixing bowl with seal and use as needed.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
(Let rise about 20 minutes before baking.)

title: apple jelly pie
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar
and jelly.
Add eggs.
Pour in pie shell and cook in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: super scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet melt the margarine over a medium heat, saute the onion until tender.
Stir in the soup and milk, stir until creamy, then add the potatoes.
Add the green pepper, pimiento, 1 cup of cheese and 1/2 of the crumbs.
Stir together, pour into a shallow pan sprayed with PAM.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese and cracker crumbe over the top.
Bake at 375° for about 40 - 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar (1/4 cup brown and 1/4 cup white), pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup water and add to mixture, mixing well.
Let cool, then add beaten egg whites to which 1/2 cup white sugar has been added gradually.
Put in baked cooled pie shell.
Place in refrigerator until needed.

title: deviled lamb shanks
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy saucepan, heat oil and brown lamb on all sides, removing shanks to make room for others as they are browned.
When all shanks have been browned and removed, add onions and garlic and saute, stirring until onions are golden. Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Return lamb shanks to Dutch oven, turning to coat with sauce.
Bring to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until lamb
is tender. Remove cover and cook over medium heat until sauce is thickened and coats lamb shanks about 20 minutes longer.
If there is a lot of fat on top of the sauce, spoon it off before reducing the sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic in a small amount of fat.
Drain and add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.

title: dilly chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and sprouts.
Cut pita bread in half.
Spoon mixture into pocket.
Top with sprouts. Makes 4 servings, 280 calories per serving.
Fat content:
10%. Here's to healthy eating.
Enjoy!

title: banana ale
directions: Boil water and sugar 3 minutes.
Add juices and chill at least 3 hours.
Put in freezer.
When serving, mix 1/2 punch mixture and 1/2 ginger ale.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat for 4 minutes; stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not underbake!

title: steamed barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown meat on both sides in large frying pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cook on high until steaming, then reduce to simmer and cook until done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt; let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
(Can add 5 to 6 marshmallows, if desired.)
Add oatmeal and vanilla. Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: fricassee
directions: Measure hot water into stew pot.
Add salt, pepper, ginger, parsley flakes, butter and turkey necks.
Simmer until almost tender.
Add vegetables; cook according to bag instructions.
In saucer, add broth to flour, making a semi-thin solution.
Add flour-broth solution to thicken slightly.

title: frozen fruit cake
directions: Chill cream for whipping.
Scald milk in top of double boiler. Mix together flour, sugar and salt; add to milk and cook over water until thickened.
Stir in beaten eggs and cook until thick. Add vanilla.
Cool.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
(Do not bake yet.)
Spread 1/2 dough mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at temperature stated on package for 20 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix and put into 2 loaf tins.
Let rise 25 minutes.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes.
Raise heat to 350° for 15 minutes.
This can be baked in tin cans; cut off the other end after baking and they come out easily.
Be sure to spray the tins. Makes nice little gifts.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Melt together and boil, on High in microwave for 2 minutes, the brown sugar, Karo syrup and margarine.
Add soda and stir.
Pour and mix over popcorn.
Put in a large brown sack in microwave for 4 1/2 minutes.
Shake every 45 seconds.
Spread out to cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Brown onions, celery and pepper.
Add broth, soups, chili powder and chicken.
Mix well.
Let simmer while spaghetti cools.
Drain well and add to chicken mixture. Bake in casserole dish.
Can be topped with sliced cheese for flavor.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda together.
Add 1 cup buttermilk and water; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 uncooked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add Special K cereal.
You may need a little more.
Pat into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together in casserole dish and top with 2 cups of Rice Krispies.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Soak garbanzos overnight with a tablespoon of salt in sufficient water to cover beans.
When ready to cook, drain the salted water from the beans and place them with the beef bone and ham bone in 2 quarts of water.
Cook for 45 minutes over slow fire.
Fry the white bacon with paprika and onion and add to the beans with the potatoes, saffron and salt to taste.
When potatoes are done, remove from fire and add chorizo.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in the order listed.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Bake in deep 10-inch pie pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
No crust needed.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields 2 cups mix.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of fat from bacon.
Place cut up potatoes, crumbled bacon, onion and enough water in pan to cook potatoes until tender.
When they are tender, add milk, butter, salt and pepper.

title: date rolled cookies
directions: Chill dough well. Spread with the filling and slice. Bake at 350°.

title: chickpea dip (hummus)
directions: Drain the chickpeas thoroughly, reserving the liquid.
Combine the chickpeas with the other ingredients in a blender jar.
Blend until creamy.
If necessary, add some of the liquid from the chickpeas to reach the desired consistency.
Serve chilled and sprinkle with chopped parsley as a dip for raw vegetables, or as a spread.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast in pan with lid at 250° to 300° for about 4 hours.
Done when starts to brown. Take meat out of juices, slice and leave in juices in refrigerator at least 4 hours or overnight. Simmer in crock-pot several hours.
Serve on hard rolls with mild pepperoncini.

title: chicken mull
directions: Boil chicken and onions in 4 cups salt water, about 2 1/2 hours.
When meat leaves the bone, remove from broth.
Reduce heat.
Chop chicken and return to broth.
Add other ingredients in order given.
(Add saltines until Mull is thick.)
Let reach boiling point, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to warm.
Can be reheated several times.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put shrimp in blender.
Add 8 ounces sour cream.
Mix together.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Serve with Town House or Ritz crackers.

title: strange chicken
directions: Grease baking dish and line with dried beef. Wrap chicken breast with bacon. Lay on top of dried beef. Mix sour cream with cream of celery soup undiluted.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion and pepper.
Brown diced onions and peppers in frypan.
Add to other mixture.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Use bacon on top if desired.

title: sugar-free peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches with melted margarine.
Stir flour, baking powder, milk and Equal together.
Spread peach mixture in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Pour batter over peach mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: bootleg beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry in a skillet until about half done.
Add onion.
When the onion is slightly brown, pour off all fat.
Add a can of pork and beans, brown sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Stir well and cover.
Let simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: prune bars
directions: Beat eggs and add oil and sugar.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in baby food.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafood newburg(this recipe has been altered for low calorie diets.)
directions: Make a white sauce of the margarine, flour and milk.
Bring just to boiling and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir slowly to keep mixture cooking evenly.
(Do not overcook as sauce will curdle.)
Add imitation crab, mushrooms, onions, lemon juice, salt and pepper and mix well.
Serve over hot buttermilk biscuits. Serves 12.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet with metal handle or heatproof serving dish, melt butter.
Add oil, half the parsley, garlic powder, salt, red pepper and lemon juice; mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently with butter mixture.
Arrange in skillet in single layer.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or just until tender. Sprinkle with rest of chopped parsley.
Bring skillet to the table.
Garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine to consistency of mayonnaise, then add sugar while continuing beating.
While beating, add eggs; beat well and then add vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Take sour cream and mix into the margarine mixture.
Then start adding flour mixture ingredients with creamed ingredients slowly.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 400° for minutes.

title: vegetable fruit muffins
directions: Place in a large bowl all your vegetables and fruits. Add and stir in flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix together the eggs and oil. Blend together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: royal icing
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in small sauce pan. Add remaining ingredients, stir and let come to boil on medium heat. Stir until thick. Serve warm! Store in jars or small containers; keeps for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: crab imperial
directions: Clean crabmeat of all shells.
Mix together all rest of ingredients.
Fold crabmeat into the vegetable, sauce mixture. Put into individual or 1 large casserole dish.
Bake at 375° until puffed and browned, about 25 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with cream, ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer and cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables until done, but not browned.
Blend in flour, dry mustard and chicken stock; cook 5 minutes.
Blend in cheeses and beer.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Season and serve with French bread and tossed salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli until light green.
Lay in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix soup and mayonnaise; pour and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle with pecans and cheese.
Mix crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; pour melted butter over this and mix together.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with crushed pecans or walnuts before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven meatball stew
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, green pepper, cornmeal, salt, dry mustard and chili
powder; shape into meatballs.
Brown in hot fat.
Place in
casserole
dish.
Add
flour to fat in skillet and tomato juice;
pour over meatballs.
Place vegetables with meatballs.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and Crisco; add milk.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts, then 1 cup oatmeal. Gradually add second cup oatmeal.
Beat after each cup.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and remaining ingredients. Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and cover with foil. Freeze until firm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: zucchini-chip omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet melt butter and saute onion
and
garlic
until golden brown.
Remove garlic. Add zucchini,
salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, 5 to 7 minutes until zucchini is fork-tender. Beat eggs with milk and cheese. Combine zucchini
and
egg
mixture
in 1 1/2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with potato chips and paprika.
Bake about 20 minutes until firm and set.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil; turn down heat.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally until cabbage is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked tuna-cheese sandwich
directions: Combine cheese, tuna and other ingredients; blend with a fork. Spread on buns that have been cut in half lengthwise.
Wrap each bun in aluminum foil and place on baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve on warm dish and garnish with pickle, carrot curls or radish roses.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble enough biscuits to fill an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla; pour over crumbled biscuits.
Mix well. Bake in oven at 425° until slightly dry or until crumbs have browned.

title: ground beef delight
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add garlic salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Grease baking dish and put in layers of noodles, meat sauce, sour cream mix and grated cheese, ending with grated cheese on top (2 layers of each).
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in oiled loaf pan at 350° to 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Make a cream sauce of milk, flour and butter.
Put salmon into bowl.
Add sauce, lemon juice and seasoning.
Mix with fork until salmon is well-broken.
When cool, mold into desired shape.
Roll in bread crumbs, then in egg, beaten with 1 tablespoon milk and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep, hot fat.

title: chicken and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Combine spinach, sour cream, cheese and nutmeg.
Spread over potatoes.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Heat through and put in hot jars and seal.

title: frozen pear salad
directions: Drain pears and heat pear liquid to pour over jello.
Soften cream cheese and put in hot liquid.
Beat until smooth.
Mash pears and add to ingredients.
Fold in the 1/2 pint whipped cream. Refrigerate but do not freeze.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan; dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: * M&M's with nuts is best but can use plain.

title: perfect roast beef
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Salt and pepper roast, which should be at room temperature, so take out of refrigerator early.
Place roast on rack in a shallow baking dish and put in oven.
Roast for 1 hour, then turn oven off.
Do not open door; it ruins the whole process.
Allow 3 hours in oven to complete cooking.
It can go a little longer, if needed.
About 20 minutes before you want dinner on the table, turn the oven back on to 300° to warm up roast.

title: salsa
directions: Place tomatoes in blender.
Add onion, jalapenos, garlic, chiles, salt and pepper.
Blend slowly until desired consistency. Pour in bowl and put in fridge. overnight.
The colder it is, the hotter.
This is a basic salsa recipe.
You can add or subtract any ingredient.
You can also add fresh cilantro.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In pie plate or shallow casserole, spread cooked broccoli and top with chicken.
Combine soup, milk and water chestnuts and about half of cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Combine margarine and crumbs.
Spread over cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° or until hot.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cheese and Equal.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with water so they'll stick together and press into pie pan to form a crust.
Mix milk and pudding by hand.
Add pumpkin, Equal and spices.
Spread pumpkin mixture in bottom of crust. Spread cheese mixture over that and chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
cover.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg yolk and beat well.
Gradually add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields about 8 dozen.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, soup and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix in broccoli and chicken.
Cover with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: tuna-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and place in shallow 2-quart casserole. Add tuna.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Stir together sugar, margarine, dates and coconut and cook over low heat until it boils.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies and pecans. Roll in balls in the powdered sugar.
Deeelicious!

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and peppermint extract, blending well.

title: shrimp over rice
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute onion and celery in margarine over medium heat until tender.
Add cornstarch and mix thoroughly. Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add milk and cook until it thickens.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: ray's chili
directions: Combine ground meat, chopped onions and oil; cook until meat is brown.
Combine all ingredients and simmer minimum of two hours until thickened, stirring often during cooking.
Best the next day.
Makes about 8 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients in pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Last 15 minutes, add crushed potato chips on top.

title: hawaiian tapioca with custard cream
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients; let stand 5 minutes to soften tapioca.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens and begins to boil, about 5 minutes. Add wine and continue cooking 5 more minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon pudding into six 12 ounce wine glasses or dessert bowls.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled, about 2 hours.

title: southwest chicken rice bake
directions: Cut chicken in cubes.
Brown in oil in large skillet.
Remove chicken.
Brown peppers and onion in same skillet with oil.
Cook until tender.
Add garlic, cumin, cinnamon, chili powder, bouillon, tomatoes and rice.
Bring to boil, then boil for 5 minutes.
Turn into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover, spread salsa evenly over top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and black olives.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt cream cheese and milk in a small pan.
Add Parmesan cheese and onion salt.
Stir well until all is melted.
Pour over vegetables, etc.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and let stand a few hours.

title: toasted "cheese" sandwich filling
directions: Blend until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Make "cheese" sandwich with whole grain bread.
May add soy mayonnaise and sliced tomato.

title: best bran muffins
directions: Combine oats, flour, wheat flour, cereal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, combine egg, oil, molasses, buttermilk and pineapple.
Pour into the dry mixture and blend until all particles are moistened.
Stir in raisins or nuts. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Heat crock-pot and fill with peeled and cored apples. Add spices. Cook all day, stirring occasionally. Remove lid and allow to thicken. Remove from crock-pot and put in airtight jars or refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put Karo and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
After mixed, pour over corn flakes. Make small balls.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy and marshmallows in double boiler or microwave.
Add condensed milk and pour in ice cream freezer.
Add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Melt all ingredients in a saucepan (except ice cream).
Then beat in ice cream.
Put 2 to 3 teaspoons of mixture in a cup of hot water.
Add 1/2 or 1 jigger of rum.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on lettuce with party crackers.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Add grated rind and juice of lemons.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour gradually, beating hard after each addition.
Add butter and place in double boiler; cook until thick.
When cool, spread between layers.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Steam or boil fresh broccoli.
While broccoli is cooking, combine margarine, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk gradually and then cheese.
Stir until cheese melts and sauce thickens. Pour over drained broccoli.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Mix sugars, lard and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda, salt into sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal last.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Grease and flour pan.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in 2-quart saucepan until bacon is crisp.
Add enough water, if necessary, to reserved clam juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir clams, liquid, potatoes and pepper into onion mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and boil until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Heat, stirring occasionally, just until hot.
Do not boil.

title: baked cheese and meat souffle(quiche)
directions: Beat eggs, milk and seasoning together.
Put bread, margarine, cheese and meat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread, etc.; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chitlens
directions: Fill a large basin with cold water.
Drop in chitlens and soak for 30 minutes.
Drain off water.

With a sharp paring knife, pull off fat under running water and discard the fat from the chitlens. Rinse the meat again with cold running water and let soak for 1 hour, changing the water several times.
Rinse the meat again under cold running water and place in a large Dutch oven or crockpot. (Chitlens should be thoroughly clean.)
Cover with water; add onion, vinegar, hot pepper pod, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 hours or until chitlens are fork-tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef-macaroni italiano
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown ground beef until cooked and crumbly.
In large saucepan, melt butter and blend flour.
Stir in undrained stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, red wine, onion soup mix, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in beef and macaroni.
Spoon into
a large casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, top with pepper rings.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Save the water the chicken was boiled in to boil the vegetables.
Place all of the ingredients (except corn starch and peas) in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Mix corn starch in 1/2 cup cold water and add to pot as a thickener.
Add small can of peas and salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat and pour into 2 of the pie crusts.
Top with 2 remaining crusts.
Cut slits in top for steam to escape.
Bake at 350° until tops are brown and filling is steaming hot.
Place on cookie sheet to avoid excess spillage.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Fry and drain ground beef and onion.
Add jar of sauce and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add a little spaghetti sauce to noodles.
Mix. Put half noodles in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put a layer of Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Put the remaining noodles over cheese.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate over bottom of pie shell.
In a bowl, mix syrup, sugar and eggs; stir in margarine.
Pour over mixture in pie shell.
Bake 1 hour or until filling is set.
Cool on wire rack.
May top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate gelatin angel food torte
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Melt chocolate in hot water. Add gelatin to chocolate and cool.
Beat egg yolks and add to chocolate.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar to beaten egg whites; beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold the egg whites into gelatin mixture.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese, then mix all ingredients together. Use hands to make into balls about the size of a dime.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
These can be made into balls, put on a cookie sheet and frozen. Then remove balls and put in bag to store in freezer until needed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef up fine.
Mix all other ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: duane's italian steak dinner
directions: Sprinkle steak with broiled steak seasoning and slice into thin strips.
Saute with onion and margarine.
Add other ingredients and the spices to taste.
Lower heat and cover and simmer until done.
Thicken with paste of flour and water. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: curried chicken
directions: Heat oil. Add onion, garlic and curry powder.
Cook 5 minutes, stir gently.
Add chicken, brown and remove (keep warm).
Add tomatoes to oil mixture, stirring constantly (3 minutes).
Add hot water and salt; mix.
Add chicken and simmer until tender (50 minutes).
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Blend evaporated milk into flour; stir constantly.
Stir and cook until thickens. Serves 6.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in large bowl.
Add dates, orange slices and nuts.
Stir to coat each piece.
Add flour mixture and coconut to cream mixture.
Put in a greased and floured tube pan and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 (3 ounce) box of raspberry Jell-O.
Cool and fold in 6 sliced bananas and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into 2 cooked pie shells or graham cracker crust.
Chill well.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: continental turkey
directions: Preheat electric frypan to 300°.
Saute green onions, celery and green peppers in margarine.
As vegetables begin to brown, add almonds, chestnuts and turkey.
Blend well together.
Add salt, pepper, flour, paprika, curry powder and sweet basil.
Allow to brown lightly, stirring constantly.
Add poultry broth, pimentos and pineapple.
Mix well.
Cover; open vent, bake at simmering point until hot and bubbly (about 20 minutes).
Serve with rice or hot parsley biscuits.
Makes 8 to 19 servings.

title: cheese marinade
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Mix all ingredients except onion rings.
Pour mixture over onion rings and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Make about 4 cups rings.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in brown sugar, white sugar and oatmeal. Mix.
Press in 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes at 350° until bubbling.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread on top.
Cut before refrigerating.

title: joyce's easy stroganoff
directions: Prepare the rice according to the instructions on Uncle Ben's rice box.
Saute ground beef and chopped onion in a skillet. Drain and add the mushroom soup and sour cream.
Salt to taste.
Stir to mix and heat until bubbly. Serve over rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender (do not drain), add all other ingredients and stir.
Pour in 11 x 14 inch baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° - 400° until it bubbles all over.
Do not over cook --will be dry.
May need to add more water before baking.
Should be soupy when put in oven.
Serves about 10 -15.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into two loaves.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt bill's brown candy
directions: Melt 1 pint sugar in iron pan, slowly, to a light brown syrup. Meanwhile, cook other 2 pints sugar and milk over slow fire.
Use heavy pan large enough for all the mixture.
Pour melted sugar into boiling milk very slowly, stir constantly.
Watch for curds. Continue stirring at slow boil to firm ball stage.
Turn out fire and add soda, stir vigorously as it foams.
Add butter, stirring as it melts.
Set aside and let cool for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and pour into pans.

title: fruit slush
directions: *May substitute with strawberries, blackberries, peaches or any fresh fruit, such as banana and pears.
Only limited by your imagination.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pan and shape with hands.

title: antipasto
directions: Cook carrots and celery in a mixture of half water and half vinegar until tender, but firm.
Cool.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl; toss thoroughly and let stand for 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	and chill.
Make early, preferably the night before you use it.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender in order listed.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured glass pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Spread rhubarb in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and dry jello over the top of the rhubarb.
Then add dry cake mix over jello mixture.
Drizzle water and margarine over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chilli steaks
directions: Sear steaks in hot oil,
both sides and place steaks on baking dish.
Spread one
teaspoon
of chillies on each steak. Add sliced onions on top of chillies.	Place sliced Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese starts to brown.

title: baked farfalie and olives(makes 6 servings.)
directions: Cook farfalie in boiling water until tender; drain.
Toss with Parmesan cheese gently.
Add Swiss, Cheddar and chopped olives; mix well.
Spoon half of the farfalie mixture into a greased 3 quart baking dish.
Top with half the white sauce.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serve garnished with sliced stuffed olives.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams; save juice.
Soften cheese at room temperature. Mix with mayonnaise and combine all remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Gradually add 1/4 cup clam juice, if thinner dip is desired.
Chill.
Serve with chips.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: boston bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Add celery and onion. Blend remaining ingredients, except bacon, in shaker/blender, etc.
Pour dressing over beans. Crumble bacon on top.
Chill overnight.

title: mimi's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, margarine and almonds. Top with crackers.
Top the crackers with melted margarine and sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken that crossed the road
directions: Fry chicken pieces in olive oil, browning with salt, pepper and lots of Italian seasonings.
Remove. Saute the mushrooms, onion, olives and parsley.
Add the white wine.
Turn heat down and cook until thickens slightly.
Pour mixture over chicken and refrigerate overnight for chicken to absorb flavors.
Cut top off and remove bread from loaf.
Stuff with sauce on the bottom, then the chicken.
Top with lid.
Wrap with foil and bake in oven at 300° to 350° to heat about 1 hour.

title: lemon pudding with blueberry sauce(low-fat)
directions: Beat egg substitute at high speed of an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add 1/4 cup sugar; beat 1 minute.
Add milk and next 3 ingredients; beat well.
Add flour; beat until well blended.
Pour half the mixture into each of 2 (6 ounce) custard cups or ramekins coated with cooking spray.
Place custard cups in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Add water to pan to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.
Remove cups from water; set aside. Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and next 4 ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl; stir well.
Add blueberries; stir well. Microwave at High 3 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes.
Spoon half of the mixture over each pudding.
Yield:
2 servings.
Calories:
Fat:
2.4 grams.

title: sour cream squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: gook
directions: Halve cucumbers lengthwise and slice.
Bite size slice celery, bell peppers, tomatoes and onions.
In very large bowl, mix vinegar and sugar.
Add veggies; fill remainder of bowl with water.
Mix very well.
Refrigerate 4 hours and serve.
Great for summertime get togethers.

title: 15 minute pie
directions: Mix all but Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip.
Put into browned, cool pie shells or cookie pie shells.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or all day.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; add rhubarb.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones.
Mix with cream of chicken soup and 1 soup can of milk.
Put in baking dish.
Cook Stove Top stuffing mix as directed on package.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: smoky links appetizers
directions: Combine and heat in crock-pot until thick and hot (45 to 50 minutes).

title: canned peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in cobbler pan, then pour in peaches.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, nutmeg and milk together and pour over peaches.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: homemade reese's cups
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Melt chocolate morsels.
Spread peanut butter mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour melted chocolate on top.
Spread across.
Let stand until chocolate is hardened.
Cut into squares.

title: coffee mocha punch
directions: Warm 1
cup
chocolate milk;
stir in coffee and almond extract.
Blend
well with remaining chocolate milk.
In punch bowl place
gallon
of vanilla ice cream.
Pour milk over ice cream.
Cover with scoops of remaining ice cream.
Garnish with dollops
of
whipped
topping
and sprinkle with nutmeg. Yields 2 gallons.

title: spam casserole
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes.

title: pear conserves
directions: Mix all ingredients except walnuts in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Boil uncovered, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly (25 to 30 minutes). Stir in walnuts.
Immediately pour mixture into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe rim of jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: big island stew
directions: Brown onions, green pepper and ground beef in oil.
Add all vegetables, steak sauce, a pinch of basil and dried mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Do not use metal or refrigerate.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix yeast and water;
then
add sugar and flour.
Knead on floured surface and let raise in warm space for 30 minutes. Heat oven to 400°.
Fill
pot
full
of water; add baking soda and bring to
a
boil.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut and twist into pretzel shapes.
Place on slotted spoon and lower
into boiling water
for
to
seconds.
Place
on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: martha's chicken dumplings
directions: Sift flour and dry milk; cut in Crisco.
Stir in water, one tablespoon at a time, until dough clings.
Knead 18 to 20 strokes; roll out and cut in 2-inch squares.
Drop in boiling chicken broth.
Lower heat and cover.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce and zucchini.
Spread 1 cup mixture in baking dish.
Top with 3 uncooked noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and form a ball.
Dice beef and roll ball in beef.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: curried potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into 1/2-inch cubes (makes about 5 cups). Place in a small bowl with green beans.
Combine yogurt, salt, curry powder, garlic powder, white pepper and turmeric.
Pour over potatoes; toss to coat.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, at least 30 minutes.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: cocoa krispie bars
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add Cocoa Krispies.
Quickly stir and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion until tender.
Drain.
Add cream of celery soup, cheese and eggs.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt margarine and crumble crackers in it.
Spread on top of casserole. Cook in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mex-tex corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add milk to make mixture thin enough to spoon into muffins or pour into pan.
Cook until lightly brown on top at 450°.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a Bundt pan, put a layer of nuts.
Cut biscuits into 6 pieces and roll into mixture of sugar and cinnamon, then put one can of biscuits onto nuts.
Put another layer of nuts and then another layer of biscuits.
Top with nuts.
In saucepan put brown sugar, water and oleo.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Put out on plate to cool.

title: easy orange cake
directions: Instead of the water called for in the recipe on the cake mix box, use the can of mandarin oranges including the liquid and oranges.
Just dump them into the mix and blend and cook as directed.

title: grape juice(uncooked)
directions: Stem grapes.
Put grapes and sugar in hot quart canning jars. Fill with boiling water and seal.
Invert jars a few hours.
Ready to use in 6 weeks.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Blend together the 3 tablespoons Crisco, 1/3 cup sugar, egg and 1 teaspoon salt. Sift 1 1/2 cups flour with the baking powder. Add milk and mix. Spread in greased 9-inch square cake pan.

title: strawberry-lemonade witch
directions: Blend first three ingredients in the blender and then slowly blend in ginger ale.

title: spiced cider
directions: Bring water, spices and sugar to a boil. Add juices and cider. Simmer for at least half hour. Serve warm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beating until smooth.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add bananas and mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 3/4 of an hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown and drain sausage; spread over bread crumbs.
Spread one cup cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add salt and pepper and pour this mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Spread one tube crescent rolls in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat egg yolk, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Spread over rolls.
Take second tube of crescent rolls and lay on top of cheese mixture.
Beat egg white with a fork and spread on top. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup nuts and sprinkle over top of egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: chocolate fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Sift together several times the flour, salt, baking powder and 1 1/2 tablespoons of cocoa.
Add to creamed sugar and butter mixture alternately with the milk.
Pour into a greased cake pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Mix together brown sugar, white sugar and 4 tablespoons of cocoa. Spread over top of cake mixture.
Pour the 1 1/2 cups boiling water over all.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Turn upside down.
Serves 9.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs beating well.
Add vinegar and food coloring to sugar mixture.
Set aside.
Sift together all dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to sugar mixture, mixing well after each.
Add vanilla.
Place in 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix soup, cheese and milk.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Separate rolls and place chicken on each roll.
Roll up.
Tuck in edges.
Put rolled up chicken on top of mixture.
Pour remaining 1/2 mixture over rolls.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizzelles
directions: Grease pizzelle iron.
Heat pizzelle iron according to manufacturer's directions.
(You can also use a krumkake iron instead of pizzelle iron.)
Mix all ingredients.
Drop 1 tablespoon batter onto heated pizzelle iron and close iron.
Bake about 30 seconds or until golden brown.
Carefully remove pizzelle from iron; cool.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen, 75 calories per cookie.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Roll box of vanilla wafers until fine crumbs.
Cut up fruit in a large pan.
Add crumbs and mix well.
Melt butter and marshmallows in a double boiler.
Pour over mixture and mix well. Then press in a well-greased pan.
Let set in refrigerator at least 48 hours before cutting.

title: old fashioned molasses taffy
