directions: Combine molasses, butter, sugar and vinegar. Cook to light-crack stage. Remove from heat. Stir in soda and flavoring. Turn onto buttered platters and cool until you can take it up in your hands. Pull until cream colored, then twist. This is fun to pull with 2 people.

title: friday night dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks.
Add tomatoes (cut up if whole). Microwave on High, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted. Add chili and stir well.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: kraut slaw
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill; best to let set overnight.
Can add more sugar, if you like.

title: alison's fast, fun and healthy pasta salad
directions: How to make it:
Prepare the pasta according to package directions; drain and let cool for a few minutes.
Mix the pasta, vegetables and tomatoes together.
Toss the whole thing with the fat-free dressing.
(You can use as much or as little as you like, but make sure that you use at least enough to coat the pasta, or it will stick together in an ugly and congealed lump!)

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger in frying pan; drain.
Add to all of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes servings for about 12 or you can half the recipe.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots; drain and place in layers in glass roasting pan or large Corning pan.
Top with thinly sliced onion and green pepper.
Repeat layering.
Mix other ingredients; pour over carrots.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Taste improves with age.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and mashed bananas until smooth.
Fold into cream mixture.
Sift flour.
Second measure: Add soda and baking powder and sift again.
Alternately add with buttermilk into cream mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix well. Use two (9-inch) pans or long loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: In saucepan combine brown sugar, gelatin, salt and spices. In bowl combine egg yolks and milk.
Stir into brown sugar mix and cook stirring constantly until it comes to a boil, remove from heat, stir in pumpkin.
Let set and chill until it mounds slightly.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form gradually.
Add sugar beating at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Then fold into pumpkin mixture thoroughly.
Turn into baked crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Pour into iron skillet and bake until well done.

title: chocolate hershey dessert
directions: Bake graham cracker crust 8 to 10 minutes in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat milk to scalding; add corn meal.
Gradually add butter, salt and sugar.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add small amount of hot corn meal mixture and mix well.
Add remaining hot mixture, stirring until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately with butter.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 cup sugar and set aside.
Melt 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/3 cup sugar and butter until sugar dissolves and then add nuts.
Cut 1 can of biscuits into quarters.
Roll in dry mixture.
Place in bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan or round 9-inch cake pan.
Spread half of butter mixture over this.
Cut other can of biscuits in quarters and place in pan.
Pour remaining mixture over biscuits.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into saucepan; bring to a rolling boil, stirring often.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Stir mixture until candy starts to thicken.
Drop mixture quickly onto wax paper and cool.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 1 1/2 tablespoons of mix per cup of hot water.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate. Spread cocktail sauce on cream cheese. Layer with shrimp, green onion, bell pepper and tomato. Top with grated Mozzarella cheese. Chill. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: mexican rabbit
directions: Boil rabbit in salted water; bone and place in bottom of baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Chop onion over rabbit.
Slice the cheese thin and place over onion; sprinkle 1/2 package Doritos over cheese.
Pour soups over all (no water); pour tomatoes/chilies over soups.
Top with rest of crushed Doritos. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Fold in whipped topping; spoon into crust. Top with pie filling. Refrigerate until serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Let orange jello, lemon jello, boiling water and ginger ale partly set.
Mix in pineapple, pecans and marshmallows. Refrigerate.
Mix sugar, flour, pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook until thickened.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed; then fold in pineapple mixture.
Spread over jello salad; refrigerate until well chilled.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Put the chicken breasts in large Pyrex dish.
Chop onion and green pepper and put over the top.
Drain mushrooms and pour on top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel devil's food cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into mixing bowl; beat until creamy. Makes 3 nice layers (8-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Spread caramel filling or white cream cheese frosting.
(Recipe is 60 years old and very good.)

title: old-fashioned carrot cake(pillsbury winner)
directions: At least 2 days before serving, put raisins in a medium saucepan with brandy.
Soak overnight at room temperature.
The next day, add water, sugar, butter, carrots and spices.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Cover and let stand at room temperature overnight.
The next day, heat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch angel food tube or 12-cup fluted pan.
Add walnuts, flour, baking powder, soda and salt to carrot mixture.
Mix thoroughly.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Chop cabbage and place in casserole.
Brown meat and onion. Stir in rice.
Put on top of cabbage.
Salt to own taste.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover for first half hour and uncover for the last half hour.
Top with grated cheese the last 10 minutes, just enough to melt cheese.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In a large pan, cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add cheese and stir until melted. Remove from heat.
In a separate pan, dissolve bouillon in water. Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and cook until done.
Do not drain. Add broccoli to mixture.

title: overnight caramel coffee cake
directions: Butter a large Bundt pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the bottom of pan.
Place frozen rolls over the nuts; sprinkle pudding mix over the rolls.
Melt butter or margarine, adding brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour mixture over the rolls.
Cover pan with a damp towel and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let stand a few minutes before turning out of pan.

title: dream salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple juice, sugar and jello.
Do not remove from heat.
Add 12 chopped marshmallows until melted. Remove from heat and cool.
Add cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all and strain, except for beaten egg whites.
Fold in last and pour in two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour; mix well.
Spread evenly onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sugar at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until smooth.
Pour over partially cooled crust.
Bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 20 bars.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine
all
ingredients in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for
an
hour.
Stir every 15 minutes except the last 15 minutes, allowing it to lightly brown.
Pudding thickens as it cools. Serve warm or cold.

title: shrimp margarett
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add shrimp and tomatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup, bread, rice, parsley and onion tops.
Pour into large, well-greased baking dish.
Top with dry bread crumbs and dot with oleo.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix onions, sour cream, soup and cheese and pour over potatoes.
Brown corn flakes in melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine crushed peaches, lemon juice, sugar and almond. Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Pour mixture into a gallon ice cream freezer.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Stir thoroughly.
Freeze according to manufacturers instructions.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 can of hot Seven-Up.
Add the other can of Seven-Up when Jell-O is dissolved.
When Jell-O thickens, add sour cream, pineapple and pecans.
Coat dish with salad dressing. Pour into dish and refrigerate to congeal.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Place cooked macaroni on bottom.
Layer with hamburger.
Layer with pizza sauce.
Make sure to cover macaroni well.
Layer cheese.
Layer pepperoni.
Layer mushrooms. Sprinkle with oregano.
Make the casserole the way your family likes pizza. Use any pasta on bottom for crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Great for pot lucks!

title: black-eyed pea chowder
directions: Saute bacon with celery, green pepper and onions.
Add broth, tomatoes and peas; simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
(I cook mine longer!) Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Calories 337, fat 20 g, cholesterol 21 mg, sodium 599 mg.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Break up beef in large crock-pot, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir to blend well.
Cover and cook on high heat setting for 6 to 8 hours or low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
Yields about 10 cups.

title: salad
directions: Mix mayo and salad mix.
Mix all ingredients, except lettuce. Add lettuce before serving.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to a boil water and cocoa. Add remaining ingredients. Beat well and pour into a 10 x 14 inch pan. Bake at 400°F. for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy tuna onion fondue
directions: Mix dry soup and milk in medium saucepan; heat slowly.
When just scalded, add a small portion of cheese and stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Continue to add cheese gradually, stirring constantly, making sure each addition is melted before adding more cheese.
Add tuna and parsley.
Turn into fondue saucepan and partially cover flame so mixture is kept just warm. To serve, dip with crackers and chips.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water and set aside.
Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut a pocket in each pork chop, cutting from edge almost to bone.
Lightly season with salt and pepper.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 425° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crust:
Crush Oreos with a rolling pin between wax paper and add butter.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: By hand or with mixer, mix oleo, sugar and egg until smooth. Add salt, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves. Mix, then add zucchini and flour.
Fold in nuts or raisins.
Drop by spoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
These are soft cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in water and stew until done.
Remove from bone and cut up.
Spread mixture of butter and stuffing mix (use only 3/4 of mixture) in casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream and chicken broth from stewed chicken.
Pour this over stuffing mix; add chicken layer.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over this. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with berries and juice.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers or can be baked in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Suggest icing with confectioners sugar icing flavored with cinnamon.

title: ray's steak burgers
directions: Mix well with hands and make patties.
Have the grill nice and hot.
Cook until done.

title: georgia style brunswick stew
directions: Scramble ground sausage in heavy pot.
Add beef, scrambling so it will not lump.
When browned, drain off fat and add chicken and stock with vegetables, tomato sauce and paste.
Bring to simmer and cook for several hours in open pot. Add seasonings and hot water, if needed, while cooking.
Add beans just before serving. Serve with barbecue.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Butter baking dish; add potatoes. Saute onion; add cheese.
Mix soup, sour cream and salt and add to mixture.
Pour on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Put whole green beans, shelled limas and sliced carrots in a deep kettle.
Break up the cauliflower and cut corn off the cob; add to vegetables.
Add water to cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 25 minutes.
Drain.
While vegetables are cooking, coarsely chop tomatoes and peppers.
Peel onions and reserve.
Mix together sugar, salt, celery seed, dry mustard and turmeric in a deep kettle.
Add vinegar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in Tabasco sauce and drained vegetables, chopped vegetables and whole onions. Cook 25 minutes.
Spoon into jars and seal.
Makes approximately 7 quarts.

title: bridesmaid cake
directions: Bake pie crust on a cookie sheet (with sides).
Bake until light brown and then cool crust.
Spread jam and prepare cake mix. Spread cake mix over the jam.
Bake at 350° until cake is done. Check directions on package of mix.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Whip the cream; add salt and well drained horseradish.
Chill. Use with ham and roast beef.

title: collector's cocoa cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to cream mixture.

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice; heat and mix with jello.
Add other ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: dandelion salad
directions: Place washed greens in salad bowl.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over dandelion greens.
Mix well and serve hot.

title: nectarine pineapple conserves
directions: Pit nectarines; do not peel. Finely chop or grind, using coarse blade. (Or dice about 1/2 cup at a time in processor until they are finely crushed, not smooth.) Measure fruit; should be 3 cups. Combine with undrained pineapple, lemon juice, cherries and sugar in a large kettle. Heat to boiling, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil hard for 1

minute. Remove from heat and stir in pectin. Stir and skim off foam for 7 minutes. Pour into hot, sterilized glass jars and seal at once. You may pour a thin layer of melted paraffin over tops of jars. When cool, add a lid and seal it. Makes 9 jelly jars.

title: granny's tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes until they will easily break apart with fork. Break or mash tomatoes and bread until thickened.
Let simmer, then add honey.
Continue to simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.
Don't thicken too much.
Should be a medium thickness.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread over fresh sourdough or French bread.

title: nut & honey crunch cereal date bars
directions: In a 2-quart pan, combine dates, orange juice, 1/4 cup brown sugar and cloves.
Cook at medium heat, stir occasionally until boiling.
Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes or until thick.
Cool. Combine the flour, cereal, 1/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
Add syrup.
Mix well.
Pat 1/2 of cereal mixture in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan, spread date filling over crust.
Pat remaining cereal mixture over top and press firmly.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken parts.
In a bowl, combine flour and paprika.
Drain liquid from yogurt.
Place in another bowl. Combine mashed potato buds, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning and salt and pepper in a third bowl.
First, dredge the skinned chicken parts in flour mixture.
Then dip the chicken into the yogurt.
Finally roll the chicken into the potato bud mixture. Place on a nonstick pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Lightly drizzle the olive oil over the chicken. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: my aunt louise's cream cheese pound cake
directions: *For lemon flavor, substitute 1 teaspoon of lemon extract plus 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: hearty power breakfast pizza
directions: Use an even mixture of Feta cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese. Stuff peppers.
Grill until cheese melts.

title: frosted brownies
directions: In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the butter, vegetable oil and water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well. Pour into a 10x15 jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 22 minutes. Cool before frosting.

title: no yeast christmas bread(julekake-i-form)
directions: Mix flour and butter and crumble together until fine.
Add baking powder, cardamom, raisins and fruit.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Mix well. Combine remaining ingredients and mix.
Butter and flour well 2 loaf pans; fill with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Put margarine, cocoa and water in pot and bring to boil.
Pour this mixture over flour mixture and add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour cake mixture into an 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake in 400° preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Start icing 5 minutes before cake is done.
Pour over hot cake.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Arrange potatoes and carrot slices around chicken.
Sprinkle with onion.
Then place spoonfuls of mushroom soup throughout dish.
Fill can once with water and put in dish, then put mushrooms on the top.
Sprinkle with parsley, paprika and garlic powder.
Bake for approximately 1 hour (depending on chicken).
Cover for the first 1/2 hour, then uncover for remaining time at 350°.

title: lo-cal salad
directions: Put jello and pineapple in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let set in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Stir in 2 cups buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: low-cal cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Sauce:
Stir together milk, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Stir in onion.

title: penny rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, salt and hot water; stir until sugar is dissolved. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in egg and yeast.
Add 2 cups of flour. In electric mixer, beat on medium speed for two minutes.
Stir in rest of the flour.
The softer the dough, the lighter the rolls. Beat with a spoon for three minutes or until dough is smooth. Cover and let rise in a warm place until dough doubles in size. Punch down.
Cover tightly and put in refrigerator overnight or make out into rolls.

title: french bean salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Pour over rest of ingredients. Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: it can't be beet jelly
directions: In a large pan, strain beet juice and lemon juice through straining cloth. Add Sure Jell and stir. Bring to a rolling boil. Add sugar; stir and boil for 6 minutes. Keep stirring!! Remove from heat. Add Kool-Aid and stir until dissolved.

title: nine bean soup mix
directions: Combine all beans; divide into ten 2-cup packages for gift giving.
Prepare mix according to Nine Bean Soup recipe.
Yield: 10 (2 cup) packages.

title: quick macaroni saute(6 servings)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until yellow.
Add beef and cook until brown and pour off fat.
Add the rest of ingredients except for macaroni and cook on low heat for 15 minutes, partially covered.
Add macaroni and heat.
Serve with grated Cheddar or Parmesan cheese and crusty bread (Wegmans French).

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Slice potatoes (not too thin) and cover with water.
Boil just until tender.
Use 2 1/2 to 3 cups sugar and layer with potatoes and dough strips.
Before you put on last layer of dough, melt 1 stick margarine with vanilla and pour over last crust.
Dab with margarine and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease well a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecans and coconut in pan. Pour prepared cake mix over this.
Next, mix oleo, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Drop spoonfuls of this mixture on batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until tests done.
Makes a rich "gooey" cake.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan. Can frost or serve plain.

title: amish macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Rinse and drain well.

title: swedish meatballs(kottbullar)
directions: Saute onion in butter; soak bread crumbs in water.
Very important:
the bread crumbs must be plain (not Italian style). Add all remaining ingredients; combine well and shape into small meatballs.
Fry in butter, then transfer to pot.
After each batch that you fry, pour drippings from skillet onto the meatballs into the pot.
To make a gravy, you can add 1/2 can chicken stock, if desired to enhance gravy.
You can freeze this in a casserole dish and rebake later at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 as main dish.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tomatoey chicken vegetable soup
directions: Place chicken, Bloody Mary mix, tomatoes and potatoes in a large pot.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add vegetables and cook until vegetables are heated through.
This soup is low-fat and very filling.

title: white chili
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight; drain.
Place chicken in large saucepan.
Add cold water to cover and bring to a simmer.
Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin; cut into small pieces.

title: sausage-cheese snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and lightly grease a baking sheet.
Knead in a bowl to mix ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain and serve hot.

title: fay's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. In a separate bowl, mix together milk and vanilla to first mixture. Add milk and vanilla mixture alternately with dry ingredients. Drop by tablespoons onto slightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 13 minutes, depending on how large the cakes are. (Makes 5 dozen.)

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream butter with cheese.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Mix in cereal.
Press into buttered 8 or 9 inch cake pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until crisp.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: layer hot dish
directions: Layer ingredients, in order listed, except for diluted soup. Pour the cream of mushroom soup over the ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt one stick of butter and add all crumbs.
Mix.
Line casserole dish with 1 cup of mixture.
Drain asparagus and place on crumb mixture.
Sprinkle almonds on asparagus.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter.
Add flour to butter.
Stir over low heat until bubbly. Add milk and cook until slightly thickened.
Add cheese to cooked mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over asparagus.
Add remaining crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken polynesia
directions: Place Shake 'n Bake and gelatin in shaker bag; shake to blend. Coat chicken as directed on package.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Chop celery, green pepper and garlic fine and saute in oil. Mix with chicken and broth, simmer 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer another 20 minutes.

title: allen's home made chili
directions: Cook Hamburger, onion and green peppers together in a skillet until hamburger is no longer pink.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and ground beef in a crock pot.
Add water to thin if needed.
Cook on low heat for 3 hours.
Add Jalapeno Peppers or Hot Pepper Relish to taste per serving.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving the marinade; chop artichokes. Place half of the reserved marinade in saucepan; add onion and garlic.
Saute until onion is soft.
Discard garlic clove; drain. Add crumbs and seasoning to remaining marinade; stir in eggs, cheese, parsley, artichokes and onions.
Place in greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes or until set. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper. Stir in beaten eggs just till mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
In 10 skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Using 2 Tbsp. mixture for each round, cook four rounds at a time, about 2-3 min. on each side or until brown.
Makes 12 rounds or 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Rinse dried beef and pat dry.
Chop dried beef and put in the bottom of a Pam sprayed baking dish.
Wrap each piece of chicken with a piece of bacon.
Chicken can be cut to any size.
Put chicken in single layer on top of dried beef.
Mix the chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover and bake another 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: fresh fruit cream pie
directions: Prepare crust.
Mix Cool Whip with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup sour cream, gently.
Put in bottom of crust.
Prepare fruit.
Mix in a small pan, 1 cup water, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 package jello. Add cornstarch, stirring to remove all lumps.
Boil until thick. Cool and add to fruit.
Place fruit mixture over cream and chill several hours.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, and sugar.
Add eggs, oil, berries and pecans, mix until moistened.
Spoon batter into loaf pans (2) well greased.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cool in pans for 5 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Hint:
If you want to make half moon cookies, bake as shown, cool and frost flat bottom side with vanilla and chocolate frosting.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well. Use 3 to 4 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: baked chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour and brown in butter in Dutch oven.
Pour chicken soup, water, salt and pepper over chicken and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover Dutch oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together. Sift flour and add the rest of the dry ingredients to the flour. Add all dry ingredients to the creamed ingredients.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut with fancy cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Decorate.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Beat the cream cheese, eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice until smooth.
Place a vanilla wafer into cupcake liner and pour mixture over wafers.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix with Miracle Whip and hot water. Bake at 350°.
Use any frosting on top.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Combine broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Melt margarine in pan and add crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese on broccoli mixture, then top with crumbs.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until barely fork-tender (5 minutes on High in microwave).
Mix carrot, onion, squash, pimento, sour cream and soup in bowl.
Melt butter.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Layer in casserole, beginning with crumbs and ending with crumbs. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
(May bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.)
If you microwave, you may want to brown crumbs briefly under broiler.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Combine shortening and sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, then add milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add pecans, dates and cherries.
Shape into balls.
Crush corn flakes and roll each ball in flakes.
Top each cookie with 1/4 of a maraschino cherry.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti. Stir in butter and 1/2 the cheese. Spoon into serving dish/platter; top with spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach. Set aside. Mix all other ingredients. Squeeze excess juice out of spinach with fork or spin dry. Add all items together. Refrigerate. Hollow out round rye (or pumpernickel) bread. Keep bread pieces to dip. Fill hollow with Spinach Dip when ready to serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Add grated carrots, pecan nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until when toothpick is placed into cake it comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together in large baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or in slow cooker for 4 to 5 hours.

title: dr. suber's navy potatoes
directions: Cut bacon slices into 1-inch pieces.
Fry until crisp; remove from pan.
Save bacon fat.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper and continue cooking until almost tender.
Add onion and bell pepper and continue cooking until lightly browned on bottom.
Turn and brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until soft ball stage, then add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until well mixed, then pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick butter and add graham cracker crumbs and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: california sunshine pie
directions: Mix cold water and cornstarch to make a thin paste.
Combine hot water, sugar and salt in top of double boiler and bring to boil over direct heat.
Add cornstarch paste and cook until mixture begins to thicken, return to double boiler and cook until thick and smooth (about 15 minutes), stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolks, return to double boiler and add remaining egg yolks.
Cook a few minutes longer. Add fruit juices, rinds and butter and blend well.	Cool, stirring occasionally.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with 3 egg whites, 6 Tbsp. sugar and 1/4 tsp. orange rind.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well and marinate in Italian dressing for 5 minutes.
Toss with beans, ham, cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Bake in a warm oven at 300° for 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Then mix oil, sugar, soda, salt and eggs.
Then add flour, oatmeal, chocolate chips, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Mix well, then spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed saltine crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until done.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a large Pyrex bowl and on High in microwave, cook first 4 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Add next 2 ingredients and cook 2 more minutes.
Then add soda.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Break when cool.

title: wild rice soup
directions: For 2 cups cooked rice, use 2/3 cup uncooked rice; takes about 1 1/2 hours to cook.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute onions. blend in flour.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in rice and salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Blend in half and half, then dry sherry.
Heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: steak fries
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl.
Add oil to coat.
Cover potatoes generously with season-all. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400 degrees until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Let cook for 1 hour at 300°.

title: oriental spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat, onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes or until red color is out of meat and vegetables are slightly soft.
Stir in tomato paste, 7-Up, catsup and thyme.
Add thyme, mushrooms, vegetables and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well.
Then add honey and vegetable oil.
Put on two cookie sheets and roast in 250° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown, stirring several times to be sure cereal is evenly browned.
Store in tightly covered jar.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Add vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to creamed ingredients.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Combine soda, karo and water in a 3 quart saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in butter. Stir often after mixture reaches syrup stage (230°).
Add nuts when temperature reaches soft crack (280°).
Stir constantly until temperature reaches hard crack (305°).
Remove from heat, quickly stir in soda.
Beat well.
Mixture will foam up.
Pour onto 2 or 3 buttered cookie sheets.
As candy cools, stretch it out thin by lifting and pulling, using 2 forks. when cool, break into pieces. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: dijon ham 'n swiss meal in a loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat water, mustard and margarine to 125° to 130°.
Stir into flour mixture.
Mix in enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
Knead 4 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix and divide into three pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple and stir into jello.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Congeal and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli in colander and plunge into large pot of boiling water for about 10 seconds.
Drain and dip immediately into ice water to stop cooking.
Combine broccoli, carrots, cheese and bacon and toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Add mayonnaise mixture to broccoli mixture and toss well. Chill before serving.

title: ham, potato and corn soup
directions: Break bones at joints and put in a kettle with 6 cups water. Bring to boil, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bone and trim off ham bits.
Add to broth with potato and onions.
Bring again to boil and cook until potato is tender.
Add next three ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, but don't boil.

title: c.p. tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together; set aside.

title: butter green beans
directions: Steam beans until crunchy, but not cooked.
In large saute pan, heat oil and chopped garlic.
Toss green beans and cook thoroughly.
Salt to taste.

title: golden baked onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon.
Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; set aside.
Mix together the soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions; top with Swiss cheese.
Slice French bread; dip 1 side in melted margarine.
Place slices of bread (butter side up) on onions-cheese, making sure to cover completely with the bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbling and golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: light mexican stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; prick several times with fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut in half; scoop out. Combine pulp, yogurt, milk and pepper.
Mash until light and fluffy.
Stir chiles, pimentos, olives and half of Cheddar cheese into potato mixture.
Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 2 more minutes.
Contains 113 calories per half and 2.2 grams fat.

title: bob's ol-fashion peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend sugars, peanut butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat, add one level teaspoon cream of tartar, vanilla and butter or margarine. Beat with a wooden spoon until it starts to thicken.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil; add next 7 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Stir well.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut in pieces and arrange in casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, broth and Veg-All and pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and combine with flour and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls on pan.
Add next 3 ingredients in order listed. Pour eggs over all and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Serve immediately.
Delicious, nutritious and loaded with calories!!!

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients well, then add pecans and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice, omitting butter.
Cool; add onion and pepper to drained artichoke hearts.
Reserve marinade.
Cut half of artichokes.
Combine 1/2 of marinade with mayonnaise and curry, then combine all ingredients together.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add eggs, one at a time, beating between each.
Then add vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add sifted mixture alternately with cup of milk.
Spoon into large tube pan, well greased.
Bake at 300°
for 2 hours.
Let cool in pan.
Remove and wrap in aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mom's old fashioned syrup cake
directions: Sift flour with soda, salt and spices.
Set aside.
Mix syrup, sugar and oil together; beat well.
Add eggs; beat, then add flour mixture gradually while beating.
Add hot water last and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Melt the margarine.
Stir in the flour.
Spread and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and cool.
In a separate bowl, mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Spread on crust after crust is cool.
In another bowl, mix 2 packages of instant pudding with 3 cups milk.
Spread on dessert and chill.
After pudding is set, spread the remaining Cool Whip on top.
Let set for several hours before serving. Serves 20 people.

title: stew squirrel
directions: Cover squirrel with water and cook until tender.
Remove from water and cool; reserve broth.
Remove meat from bones and put back into broth.
Bring to a boil and add all other ingredients except rice.
Cook for 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add cooked rice.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers thin; slice onion thin.
Put in bowl.
In separate bowl, put sour cream and sugar and mix.
Add to cucumbers and onion.
Mix water and vinegar together and pour slowly over cucumbers.
Stir well and refrigerate.
If made one day ahead, ingredients blend better.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine next 7 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin. Stir in vanilla, raisins and pecans.
Spoon into 4 greased and floured loaf pans, medium size.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
May be frozen.

title: lemon herb cornish hens
directions: Season hens lightly with salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.
Grill hens until tender and crisp, about 1 hour, turning and basting frequently with sauce. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 inch jelly roll pan, or line pan with waxed paper.
Beat eggs until thick. Gradually beat in sugar.
Then beat in at once water and vanilla. Sift together and beat in all at once the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat just until smooth.
Pour in prepared pan and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or just until the cake tests done.
Turn immediately upside-down on towel that is sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Spread cake at once with jelly or jam, and roll up.
Keep it wrapped until cool.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine pie filling and extract in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in oven 10 to 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add shortening and milk.
Cut through shortening 6 times.
Stir in almonds; mix until dough forms a ball.
Drop dough by 6 spoonfuls onto hot pie filling.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuit topping is brown.

title: potato boats
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash them.
Add the butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Put this in the foil boats.
Sprinkle cheese on the top.
Bake until the cheese starts to melt.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Grease and flour pan, about 15 x 10-inch.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and Bisquick mix.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes.
Batter will fall just before ready to remove from oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar (optional).
Cut in squares.
Very easy to make.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers, cut off tops and remove seeds, scrape with a spoon.
Chop onion fine and add to meat, washed rice, salt, pepper and egg; mix well.
Fill green peppers 3/4 full with mixture. Place peppers in a deep pot; standing up-add tomato soup & water mixture.
Should cover the peppers, simmer about 1 hour till rice and meat are cooked.

title: twenty dollar potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Grate cooled, cooked potatoes into a bowl; set aside.
Heat butter and soup in a saucepan, stirring until smooth.
Stir in onion, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes, mixing well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with a mixture of corn flakes and melted butter.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding and whole milk until thickened, then blend in sour cream and whipped cream, one at a time.
In large deep bowl, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and mixture, usually about 3 layers. Be sure to have a layer of mixture on top.
Top with walnuts, if desired.
Chill for 1 hour.
Even better if made the night before you eat it.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Add bouillon. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add wine before serving.
Top with slice of French bread sprinkled with grated Swiss and grated fresh Parmesan cheese.
Brown slightly.
Serve hot.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except cinnamon and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar.
Pour into prepared pan and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 50 minutes.
After cooling, the bread may be wrapped and frozen.

title: dr. hart's cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Melt butter and cheese. Add Ro-Tel; mix.
Add meat.
Add 1 cup milk if too thick.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing with brown sugar, coffee, ginger, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet-sour beans
directions: Place the beans into a covered dish.
Mix and pour over the beans the sugar, salt, vinegar and oil.
Cover and let stand overnight or longer before serving.
Thinly sliced onions and green pepper strips may be added to the mixture to stand overnight or may be added just before serving.

title: lemon orange cake
directions: Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in ungreased sheet pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350°.

title: split seconds
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an electric mixer in the order given.
Divide dough into 4 parts and chill (wrapped in waxed paper).
Remove from refrigerator and shape into 4 rolls, 12-inches long and 3/4-inch thick.
Use 2 cookie sheets lined with foil. Place 2 rolls on each sheet.
Make a depression down the center of each roll with a knife handle.
Fill depression with jam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
While warm, cut diagonally into bars.
Allow to cool thoroughly on the cookie sheets.
May be frozen.

title: chicken with artichoke hearts
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons salad oil cook chicken breasts until browned on all sides.
With tongs, remove chicken to medium-sized bowl.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a casserole bowl and fill with apples, water and cinnamon.
Work together remaining ingredients until crumbly. Spread over apple mixture.
Bake for about 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve warm with cream or serve plain.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add eggs and scallions.
Stir.
Add rice, turn heat down and stir and cook until rice is heated.
Add soy sauce and salt; stir and heat for 5 minutes.
Shrimp, pork, bean sprouts, etc. can be added to rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla, mixing until thick.
Add zucchini and stir thoroughly.
Stir flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add, stirring until smooth.
Add chopped nuts and lemon rind.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure croutons; crush slightly and toss with melted margarine.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli in water, with salt added.
Remove from heat, drain well and set aside.
In another saucepan, melt cheese, stirring frequently; add soup. Stir in partially cooked broccoli.
Pour into ungreased shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crouton mixture over top.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef and pork loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in large bowl.
Put in loaf pan, cover with mixture of 1/2 cup catsup and 2 tablespoons brown sugar and bake in moderate oven (350°) for one hour.

title: lemon-poppy seed cake(low-fat)
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Moisten cornstarch with small amount of water.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool! Important!
Beat the egg whites with pinch of salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until high, firm peaks appear.
Beat in cornstarch mixture; beat until just right for topping.
Pile on top of pie.
Bake 8-inch pie at 350° until golden brown.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and egg with hand mixer until smooth. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add apples and walnuts; stir in carefully.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan; bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: reese's balls
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, sugar and butter.
Mix thoroughly and roll into balls.
Dip in chocolate bark.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix the first six ingredients.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Roll into log shape.
Chill again.
When ready to serve, roll in mixture of nuts and parsley (or just nuts, if you prefer).

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with 1/4 cup salt.
Let stand overnight; wash and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes and seal in jars.

title: mango chutney
directions: Peel and seed mango; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine with all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart pot.
Stir.
Cook, uncovered, until mushy.
Put chopped walnuts at end.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and oranges.
Add to thawed strawberries and pie filling.
Can prepare night before, but do not add bananas until ready to serve.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as normal.
When brownies are cooling down in the pan, put holes in brownies and pour Kahlua in holes (can pour some on top of brownies).
In bowl, put a layer of brownies on the bottom.
Next, put a layer of crushed Oreo cookies and Skor bars. Put a layer of Cool Whip on top of cookies and Skor bars.
Start over again with brownies.

title: pineapple pecan cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, whip cream cheese until smooth.
Gently stir in pineapple, green pepper, onions, seasonings and 1/2 cup nuts. Turn out onto a sheet of plastic wrap and shape into a ball. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Before serving, roll cheese ball in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: teriyaki sauce mix
directions: Mix ingredients all together. Pour over desired meat and marinate overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas. Spread refried beans over them.
Brown ground beef.
Add seasoning mix and tomato sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Spread over beans. Continue layers according to ingredients listed, with top layer being grated Colby cheese.
Bake, uncovered,
at 325° for 25 minutes until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and salsa.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 sugars, butter, eggs and oil and beat until well blended.
Add soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla. Gradually add flour until well blended.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Make 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool, flatten balls with bottom of glass.

title: pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Press mixture into bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan; chill.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add flour in two additions to other ingredients.
Put on floured surface.
Round up and cover with damp cloth.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Knead until springy.
Put in greased bowl; let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down; let rise again.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar and applesauce until smooth.
Blend in all remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well.
Add nuts; blend well.
Bake in 9-inch layer pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat taco bake
directions: In a skillet brown turkey and onion over medium heat.
Drain. Add the water, taco seasoning and tomato sauce and mix.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in macaroni, chilies and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until heated through.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into thin slices.
Combine all ingredients except meat.
Stir well.
Add meat and let stand for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Place in dehydrator for 6 to 8 hours or can be done in conventional oven by arranging strips on oven racks.
(Line bottom
of oven with foil.) Dry in 150° to 200° oven until dark brown and dry.
Cool and store in airtight container or in the refrigerator.

title: mexican egg bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Warm tortillas as directed on package.
Arrange in bottom of greased pan, overlapping edge of tortilla.

title: butter sauce for cake
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
May be served warm or cold.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry fruit filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Frost when cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine in pan and add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
If mixture is a little stiff, add more margarine.
Roll into balls and let chill for an hour.
For chocolate coating, melt in a double boiler the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate with a toothpick and place on cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Chill until set.

title: lakeview relish
directions: Chop tomatoes in quarters and pour salt over them and let stand while preparing rest of ingredients.
Slice onion rounds, bell peppers in eighths and hot peppers in rounds.
Drain salt off tomatoes, add other ingredients and simmer all until tomatoes and peppers change colors.
Pour into jars and seal or use either cold or hot-pack canning method.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Spray a 9x13 baking pan with non stick cooking spray.
Combine soup, margarine, salt, pepper, onion and cheese.
Gently mix in the potatoes and pour into prepared pan or dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Blend Bisquick and cream cheese; add milk.
Knead 10 times. Roll out on waxed paper in oval shape.
Spread jam down center. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Make a glaze out of confectioners sugar and water and drizzle over the cake while warm.
Very good and very simple.

title: jack's chilli
directions: Add ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions, shallots and bell peppers in butter until soft. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies and simmer 10 minutes.
Add crawfish and simmer 10 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 30 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 5.
May substitute shrimp or chicken.

title: cheese cloud
directions: Trim crusts from bread and arrange six slices in bottom of a greased 12x8 baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices, then with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs, add milk, mustard, onion and seasonings.
Pour over bread and let stand at room temperature for one hour.
This dish may be prepared the day before and refrigerated overnight, if more convenient.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves:

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, oleo and salt.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Pour hot mixture slowly over beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and cook 30 to 50 minutes.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of round quiche dish.
Top with chili, then salsa, cheese, green onions and black olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with round tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter pie "frozen"
directions: Mix together. Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker pie shell and freeze. Serve frozen. Can use regular pie crust, baked, if desired.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Heat tomatoes for 5 minutes.
Add butter, sugar and all seasonings.
Mix well.
Butter 2 quart casserole and fill with loosely torn
pieces of bread.
Pour tomato mixture over bread and mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly. Stir in M&M's candies and nuts.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes until browned.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Place on wire rack for cooling.

title: cheese-filled pears
directions: Drain and reserve juice.
Mix cheese and honey.
Beat until smooth.
Put inside pears and place in casserole dish.
Pour juice in dish to bake.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon or ginger.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy crab bites
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Stir well and set aside.
Trim crust from bread; cut each slice into squares. Spread each square with crabmeat mixture and place on ungreased cookie/baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: parmesan sesame sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 4 sticks; place on ungreased cookie sheets. Brush with butter, then sprinkle evenly with cheese and sesame seed. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minute sor until golden brown. Yields 4 dozen.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on bag. Drain. Combine other ingredients, saving enough cheese to top casserole.
Mix well. Pour into baking dish and cook at 325° for 30 minutes or until sides bubble and cheese melts.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Crush tomatoes and drain juice from tomatoes.
Add other ingredients and cook until thick.
Put in sterilized jars and seal in hot water bath about 15 minutes.
Very good during winter with vegetables.

title: ranch fish crackers
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Heat in oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: south of the border enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato paste, water, onion and salt.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of meat mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Place in two 12 x 20-inch baking pans.

title: bacon kraut
directions: Cut bacon up fine; fry crisp.
Remove from grease.
Put sauerkraut, brown sugar and tomatoes in casserole dish.
Mix altogether with 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Mix well and sprinkle bacon pieces over top.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, in a 350° oven.

title: grandma whiting's chocolate cookies
directions: I melt the chocolate squares first, then put everything in a bowl and mix.
Use two teaspoons to drop onto cookie sheet.
Put sprinkles or walnut meats on top or put two cookies together with vanilla icing in the middle.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
May be kept in refrigerator up to 4 weeks.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Can be frozen after cooking.
May use extra raisins if desired.

title: wassail
directions: Boil 1/2 gallon water and sugar until sugar has dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until very hot.
Makes approximately 4 gallons.

title: whole wheat pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough pulls away from bowl and forms a ball.

title: mini pizza
directions: Split muffins and toast them.
On each muffin half, put ketchup, cheese, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Put in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until melted.
If using pizza sauce, omit oregano.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Blend in egg.
Add next 6 ingredients and spread onto a greased (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While still hot, sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Let melt and spread.
Cool.
Mix 1/4 cup peanut butter, powdered sugar and 2 to 4 tablespoons milk.
Spread over the chocolate.

title: appetizer cheesecake
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in zwieback crumbs and press mixture firmly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: grandma's cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan. Pour in fruit and top with batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion and peppers in margarine.
Add cheese, which has been cut in small pieces, to spaghetti, onion and peppers while hot.
Stir in Ro-Tel.
Mix well. Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes a very large batch.
May be frozen before baking step.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in bowl. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add buttermilk; mix well. Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Roll 1/2-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425°
for 15 to 20 minutes, or until light brown.

title: milk chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.
Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: hummus(middle eastern dip)
directions: Drain and rinse chickpeas.
In a blender or food processor, combine chickpeas, juice of 1 lemon, garlic and tahini.
Blend until smooth with no lumps.
Add more lemon juice, if needed. Pour dip into bowl.
Squirt with juice of 1/2 lemon on the top and garnish with parsley.

title: chicken almondzini
directions: In saucepan, combine mayonnaise, flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk, cooking over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese and wine slowly until melted.
Saving 1/3 cup almonds for top, combine sauce with spaghetti, meat, broccoli, almonds, mushrooms and pimiento.
Place in baking dish (11 x 8 x 2-inch) topped with saved almonds and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Pour hot water over Jell-O and cool.

title: jo's pound cake
directions: Prepare 9-inch tube pan.
Grease with 1 tablespoon butter; dust with flour and set aside.

Sift flour, soda and 3/4 cup of sugar. Add the remaining butter and mix well with fingers until blended. Add lemon juice, vanilla and egg yolks one at a time and mix well with your fingers until well blended.
Beat egg whites with 1/8 teaspoon of salt until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in cream of tartar.
Add to first mixture and mix until the whites are mixed thoroughly.
Spoon into pan.
Jolt on table to remove air bubbles. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Turn off heat and let stand 10 or 15 minutes.
Remove pan to cake rack.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Loosen with spatula.
Turn on rack covered with wax paper.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown the meat and garlic in olive oil.
Stir in tomatoes, peppers, soy sauce, pepper, sugar, ginger and 3/4 cup stock. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Blend cornstarch with remaining stock.
Stir into meat mixture.
Bring to boil and simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add bananas alternately with the sifted flour mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mile high strawberry dessert
directions: Beat ingredients for no less than 15 minutes.
This mixture should fill a large mixing bowl.
Fold into this mixture 1/2 pint of whipping cream, whipped, or 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into pan, over prepared crumbs, and cover with remaining crumbs.
Put into freezer until frozen.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add seasoning mix; drain.
Begin to melt cheese in microwave or crock-pot.
Add soup, without water, to meat mixture, then add this to cheese.
Continue to cook slowly until cheese is completely melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
This recipe makes plenty.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add raspberries.
Add applesauce.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: smoked sausage & sauerkraut
directions: Simmer sausage in small amount of water to remove some more fat.
In large skillet saute' onions in oil and add a little water to stir fry.
Add remaining ingredients, except sausage.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes or until apple slices are soft.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into balls about the size of a quarter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
These can be prepared and frozen.
Just remove from freezer and put into pan. Bake as directed.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake in oven at 450° until brown on top.

title: squash and onion casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Butter a baking dish. Place layer of vegetables, then layer of crumbs, soup and cheese. Repeat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot top with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate almond brownies
directions: Melt together:
butter and chocolate, set aside.
Beat eggs, add sugar and beat, add chocolate mixture and stir well.
Add flour and salt together a little at a time mixing as you go.
Add vanilla and almond, mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Spray 8 x 8 pan, pour mixture (it will be very thick).
Bake at 350° for 25 or 26 minutes.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; add Worcestershire, sugar, Tabasco, chopped onions and chopped chipped beef.

title: coconutty macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty both mix pouches into bowl.
Add egg white, coconut extract and 1/2 cup coconut.
Mix thoroughly. Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip into egg white. Roll in coconut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press candied cherry half into center of each macaroon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until coconut browns a little. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing with spatula.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk and shortening.
Add all dry ingredients and put in 1/2 at a time.
Roll out dough and cut out.
Bake at 450°.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add zucchini, green pepper and celery.
Stir in eggplant and salt.
Remove vegetables (leaving butter in skillet) and put into casserole dish.
Add crumbs to butter.
Top vegetables with tomatoes and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of the margarine and blend in flour.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Prepare au jus mix as directed on package with 2 cups water. Add au jus gradually to flour, stirring with a whisk until thickened and smooth. Simmer 1 minute.
Add catsup, bouillon cubes dissolved in hot water, pepper, paprika and garlic powder.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Add wine and cook for 5 minutes.
Saute onions in 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine. Remove onions and keep hot.
Add remaining margarine to skillet and brown beef strips.
Add salt to taste. Combine onions and beef. Serve on a bed of rice.
Pour sauce over top.

title: pork chop and tomato gravy
directions: Open 1 can of tomato soup and spread on bottom of casserole dish or baking pan.
Layer the following:
pork chops, bell pepper, onion and soup until they are all used.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until pork chops fall apart.
Serve over rice. Good with green bean casserole.

title: bambinos
directions: I love to make them!!
Heat oven to 400°.
Spread rounds with catsup; top with pepperoni slices or sausage or just cheese. Sprinkle cheese and oregano over topping.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen canapes.
Or microwave until cheese is melted, for about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni per directions for casserole.
Add soup, mayonnaise, onion, pimento and cheese; mix together.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: In a very heavy saucepan, place butter, sugar and vanilla. Turn the burner on high and melt this mixture stirring constantly. The mixture will blend, become frothy and then turn a caramel color. Stir constantly until the mixture resembles a smooth mixture which is light brown. Do not allow the mixture
to smoke.

title: aunt fay's chow chow
directions: Chop enough green tomatoes and cabbage to have 1 gallon of each.
Chop sweet peppers and onions to have 1 quart of each. Chop hot peppers to have 2 cups (more or less to taste).
Mix all these with 1 scant cup canning salt.
Cover and let set overnight. Next day, drain well.
In large granite or stainless, mix 5 pints vinegar, 3 cups sugar, peppers, horseradish, cloves and mustard seed, all chopped vegetables and boil slowly 30 minutes.
Pack in hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal jars.
This recipe will serve 200 people.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in greased and loured bundt pan. Bake for 50 minutes at 325.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer as follows:

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Form into bite size or larger
balls.
Bake
in
oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Stick in toothpick and enjoy.

title: chicken-rotel
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Debone chicken.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add peas, mushrooms and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and add chicken.
Boil noodles in 3 cups of chicken broth until done; do not drain noodles.
Mix noodles and chicken mixture in a casserole dish. Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Can be frozen before baked.
Serves 6.

title: carrot bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Blend in eggs.
Add alternately dry ingredients with shredded carrots.
Grease and flour 3 (6 x 3-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Batter will be slightly lumpy. Spread in pie dish.

title: roast beef
directions: Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for about 4 hours. (Especially good to bake roast of pork with this.)

title: fudge lovers heaven
directions: Drop by spoonful on plate and freeze. Store in refrigerator.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix together.
Then fold in the Cool Whip, add marshmallows and mix well.
Add cherries and pecans if desired. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: stan's chili with beans
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic in Dutch oven; cook until brown and crumbled.
Add spices to tomato and bean juice, mix well and add to meat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add beans, simmer additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix sausage, eggs and crumbs and shape into balls.
Place in broiler pan and brown in oven under broiler; drain.
Mix other ingredients for sauce.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen in sauce and heated in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan by directions on package. Let cool. Punch holes in cake, then pour crushed pineapple over the cake. Next pour pudding, then top off with Cool Whip.
Spoon right out of pan to eat.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix all together and grease baking pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
When done, cut in 2-inch squares and have 1 stick of margarine melted; pour on top while in pan.
Then serve.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, syrup and sugar and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over corn.
Put corn in large roasting pan and bake 50 minutes at 250°. Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle cheeses over pie crust. Spread crabmeat and onion over cheese.
In a measuring cup or bowl with a lip, combine eggs, flour, seasonings and half and half. Carefully pour into the pie crust.
Bake 40 minutes or until custard has set.
Serves 6.

title: pork chops ragu
directions: Spray a large skillet with pam.
Add the olive oil and let warm.
Add the pork chops and sprinkle with parsley flakes, onion powder and garlic powder.
Brown chops until lightly browned on medium-high setting.
After browning, pour off all excess grease. Put the chops back into the skillet and pour Ragu sauce over the chops.
Cover pan; cook on low heat for approximately 2 hours or until tender.
Enjoy with a garden salad of lettuce, tomatoes, cucumbers, radishes and black olives.
Use Italian salad dressing. Serves 2-4 people.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken (cut up) in bottom of 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Mix soup and milk together, then pour over chicken.
Fix stuffing mix according to package instructions.
Then top casserole mixture with the stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southwestern turkey tenderloins
directions: Heat oil in 12 inch nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Cook turkey in oil 4 to 6 minutes, turning once, until brown. Stir in tomatoes, bell pepper, chili powder, sugar and lime juice; reduce heat to medium low. cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until juice of turkey is no longer pink when centers of the thickest pieces are cut. Slice turkey. Serve with sauce. Sprinkle with cilantro. This has 5 grams carbohydrates.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add soda, dissolved in buttermilk.
Mix well. Add flour, salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix in apples.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together the sausage, eggs and bread crumbs.
Form into walnut-size balls and brown on all sides.
For the sauce, mix together the ketchup, brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar.
Pour sauce over meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Or any kind of dressing.

title: cabbage hollandaise
directions: Combine salad dressing, soup, milk and salt, then heat. Meanwhile, cook cabbage 3 or 4 minutes.
Drain.
Mix corn flakes, cheese, butter and water chestnuts.
In greased casserole, layer cabbage, hot soup mixture and corn flakes mixture.
Repeat.
Top with additional grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add the can of pineapple and juice.
Add flour, sugar, brown sugar and soda.
Mix well by hand.
Pour and spread evenly in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
If you like, you can add 1 cup chopped walnuts.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender or with a mixer.
If desired, you can add 1/2 teaspoon celery seed and/or sesame seed.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: beef paprikash
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add paprika, green pepper, tomato and salt.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add water when needed to prevent sticking.

title: deviled crabs plain
directions: Heat milk and stir in enough soft white bread crumbs to make a fairly thick sauce.
Add 1/2 stick butter, salt and pepper to taste and lemon juice.
Add crab meat.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and stir in dry crumbs.
Fill shells with crab mixture and sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: tomato and garlic soup
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes on medium.
Add chicken broth; let simmer.

title: chopped steak
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Place margarine in baking dish and put into oven to melt.
Place flour, salt and pepper in Baggie. Rinse off each piece of meat and place into Baggie. Shake to coat meat with flour mixture.
Place in baking dish; cover tightly. Bake for about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: norfolk noodles
directions: Boil noodles according to directions on the package.
Drain. While noodles are still hot, mix in all the remaining ingredients except cheese and paprika.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain.
Stir in next six ingredients.
Set aside.
Separate dough into triangles.
In lightly greased 9-inch pie plate, arrange pointed ends to the center and press edges together to form a pie shell.
Beat together 2 eggs plus 1 egg white.
Put beef mixture in pie shell. Pour half of egg mixture over beef.
Arrange cheese slices on top. Spread with remaining egg mixture.
Mix reserved egg yolk with water and set aside.
Separate second package of rolls.
Roll and press into a 12-inch square.
Brush bottom of dough with egg mixture.
Place dough on top of filling.
Seal, trim and flute edges.
Brush with remaining egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: grasshopper tarts
directions: Heat chocolate chips and shortening over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted, 3 to 4 minutes.
Line 12 medium (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin cups with paper baking cups. Swirl 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture in each cup with back of spoon to coat bottom and side.
Refrigerate until firm.
Fill in with remaining chocolate.
Refrigerate until firm.
Carefully remove paper baking cups from chocolate shells.
Return shells to muffin cups.

title: herb salad dressing
directions: Chop herbs.
Pick herbs with a flavor to suit or use fines herbes blend.
Mix in blender or processor.

title: orange soda
directions: Fill your glass half full with water and the rest with orange juice.
Add one teaspoon of baking soda, stir, and now you have an orange soda.
Add sugar if you like.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry top cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of cake mix.
In a large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Press mixture evenly into bottom and halfway up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: creamy chicken
directions: In lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, arrange breasts. Place Swiss cheese on top of chicken breasts.
In saucepan, combine cream of chicken soup and 1/4 cup apple cider, stirring well. Spoon over chicken and Swiss cheese evenly.
Sprinkle dry stuffing crumbs over all. Drizzle melted butter over stuffing crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Then take out a handful and reserve for the topping.
Add liquid.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
