Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Brown roast in Dutch oven with oil.
Drain.
Add soup, horseradish, bay leaf and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes longer. Place cabbage wedges on top and cook until cabbage is tender. Remove meat and vegetables to serving platter.
Blend water and flour until smooth.
Slowly stir this into liquid in Dutch oven. Cook until thickened.

title: browned rice
directions: Brown rice in oil.
Add chopped onion, 1 can bouillon soup, 3/4 cup water and spices.
Simmer in covered pan for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook stuffing as directions say on box.
Form as crust in greased pie plate.
Put steamed broccoli over crust.
Add the milk and Egg Beaters.
(Mix these two ingredients together before pouring over broccoli.)
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until it is brown and firm. Let set for 5 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine bananas, pineapple juice and lemon juice in electric blender container; whirl 1 minute at low speed until smooth.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in a little oil.
Cook rice per package directions.

title: party chicken
directions: Place dried beef in pan. Wrap 1 piece of bacon around each breast and place on top of beef.
Mix together soup, sour cream, mushrooms and sherry.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in low oven at 250° for 1 1/2 hours. Delicious.

title: peruvian beef roast
directions: Trim eye of the round roast.
Make gashes 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart the length of the roast and in three rows.
Alternately insert slivers of raw carrot and tiny slivers of garlic.
Salt heavily and pepper.
Bake in open pan at 350° for about 3 hours or until desired doneness.
Add enough water in pan during cooking to keep from sticking but be careful not to add too much.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients. While warm, add rest of
ingredients.
Put in oblong dish and refrigerate.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Let whites stand to reach room temperature. Mix
yolks,
milk
and sugar.
With mixer on low speed, pour bourbon
and
rum
over
the
back
of
a spoon into this mixture. If
you pour it too fast, it will "fry" the eggs and make lumps. Once
it
is
all
mixed,
refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
This allows the flavors to become well acquainted with one another. About
hour
before serving time, pour this mixture into
a punch
bowl.
Whip
the
room temperature egg whites until
they form
peaks.
Lay
the
egg
whites on the yolk-milk-alcohol mixture
and
cut
through it several times with a rubber spatula. Scoop ice cream and float it on top of the egg
nog.
Garnish with
nutmeg.
When ice cream is about half melted, it's ready!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs (topping).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes, boil until soft.
In another large pan, slice onions; cover with a small amount of water and cook until tender.
Run the tomatoes and onions through straining sieve.
Mix in pepper.
Boil this mixture rapidly until it has reduced to almost half the original volume.
Place vinegar in an enamel pan; add a spice bag containing the cinnamon sticks, cloves and garlic.
Allow this to simmer about 30 minutes, then bring to a boil.
Place cover on pan and remove from heat.
Allow this to stand in pan until next steps.
When tomato mixture has cooked down to half, add vinegar mixture of which there should be 1 1/4 cups.
Add paprika, sugar and salt.
Boil rapidly until thick for about 10 minutes.
Pour while boiling into sterilized jars.
Place caps on firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: pizza salad
directions: In large bowl combine macaroni, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onions and pepperoni.
In a small bowl combine oil, Parmesan cheese, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Top with croutons just before serving.
Makes 16 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Add small onion to cucumber, also small onion (cut thin).
Add pinch of salt.
Let stand for 1 hour in refrigerator.
After hour is up, take and squeeze cucumber of excess water.
Add sour cream and sugar to taste (about 2 teaspoons); add vinegar to taste. Chill and serve.

title: green chili
directions: Brown beef well.
Add other ingredients except cheese and simmer for one hour.
Remove from
heat and stir in grated cheese. This is delicious over pinto beans, rice, macaroni, tamales, Fritos, etc.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in muffin pan in 400° oven until brown.

title: light batter
directions: Mix together water and egg.
Mix together dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients into water/egg mixture; beat with fork until smooth.
Dip vegetables into batter and deep fry at 375° to 400° until lightly browned.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Remove seeds, rinse and flatten chilies.
Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Cheddar cheese, then remaining chilies and Jack cheese.
Beat egg yolks with milk, flour, salt and pepper. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in yolk mixture.
Pour egg mixture over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until lightly browned.

title: snow balls
directions: Sift cake flour and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream butter gradually; add granulated sugar and beat, creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake in 250° oven until firm and ivory colored for 40 to 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar. Let cool and roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies and they are delicious.

title: brussels sprouts in beer(servings: 4)
directions: Trim and wash sprouts.
Place in a medium-size saucepan and pour enough beer over them to cover.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Add more beer, if needed, as liquid evaporates.
Drain.
Add salt and butter.
Serve hot.

title: pull apart caramel rolls
directions: Thaw the frozen bread dough. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear bread dough into pieces.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over pieces.
Mix together butter, brown sugar, pudding mix and milk. Pour over pieces of bread dough.
Tear second loaf of dough and put on top of first loaf.
Try to fill in empty spots.
Let rise for four hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes (very important).
Flip over onto cookie sheet.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put a layer of green tomatoes. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and Italian seasoned bread crumbs.
Make 3 layers.
On top, dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut vegetables and cover with water in a large pot.
Boil for 10 minutes, cover and lower heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
This soup is very low in calories.

title: crunchy pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, cream cheese and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavoring and 2 1/2 cups flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
Mix remaining flour with butterscotch morsels and nuts.
Fold into batter.

title: broccoli-carrot casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions.
Add milk, soup and sour cream.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then cracker crumbs, then Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix tomatoes, soups and chicken stock together; alternate layers in rectangular baking dish:
sauce, chicken, crushed chips, onion, cheese, sauce, chicken, etc.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion in a skillet.
Melt cheese and milk in microwave and combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: walnut spice kisses(cookie)
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar; mix with spices.
Fold in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased pan.
Top with 1/2 of a walnut.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana jam(yields approximately 18 ounces)
directions: Place bananas in large bowl or enameled pot.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Allow to stand for about an hour.
In a large enameled pot bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Set 3 cookies aside (crush).
Crush rest of cookies.
Mix crumbs and melted margarine into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 3 crushed cookies on top.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Freeze a second can of pineapple juice in small containers to use as "ice" in the punch.
Blend all ingredients except sherbet. Just before serving, gently add sherbet by spoonfuls.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions together for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add chicken soup, sour cream and shredded carrots.

title: cherry pie dessert
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; add to D ream Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and top with cherry pie filling.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Mix with fingers the butter, powdered sugar and flour.
After thoroughly mixed, add nuts and mix in.
Form balls and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Let cookies cool slightly, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Break and discard bottom 1/8 of each stalk.
Break remaining part into halves. Wash by soaking and rinsing.
Boil or steam until tender.
Do not overcook.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Spread a thin layer of mixture evenly over each tortilla shell. Roll up each tortilla shell.
After rolling, cut rolled up shell into 1-inch sections.
Serve with salsa dip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes. Adjust to your own taste by adding more than the specified quantities or one or more of the ingredients.

title: black chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick and
pour into a baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: open-faced tuna sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Spread on toasted bread. Use Monterey Jack or Muenster cheese on top.
Place oven on broil. Place sandwiches 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water; set aside until dissolved.
Put shortening and butter in milk, it will melt.
Combine ingredients. Knead; put in bowl.
Let rise until double; shape.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips, with electric mixer until well blended.
(Mixture will be very thick.)
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remainder of chocolate chips over top.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Frost with caramel or chocolate frosting.
Cut into bars and store in fridge.

title: plenty good polenta
directions: Slowly add polenta to boiling, salted water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cook on top of double boiler, stirring frequently, for approximately 25 minutes.
Blend in butter or olive oil.

title: skillet beans
directions: Brown diced bacon in large skillet.
Remove bits from drippings and reserve for garnish.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixture begins to bubble.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Garnish with bacon bits before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: *Can use mixture of white, brown or wild rice.
Do not use instant rice.

title: ornament cookies(decoration only)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water slowly.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes until putty-like.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters. Make a small hole at top of cookie.
Bake at 325° until light brown.
Cool.
Paint or varnish to preserve.

title: a man's casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
In large skillet, saute onion in margarine over medium flame; set aside.
Brown meat in same skillet in oil over medium-high flame; drain.
Add salt, pepper, thyme and sauteed onion to meat.
Combine soup and milk.
Arrange one-third of noodles, half of meat-onion mixture and half of soup mixture in layers in a greased 4-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Arrange remaining noodles on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° gas oven for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Yield:
8 large servings.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onions, bell peppers and salt.
Stir and let sit over night.
Drain and wash.
Add remaining ingredients to squash mixture.
Boil 6 minutes and pour into hot jars.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Chop one cup of berries.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in pan. Stir water in gradually until smooth.
Add chopped berries. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Remove from heat; stir in food coloring.
Cool in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Pour 3/4 of syrup mixture into baked pie shell.
Add remaining berries.
Pour remaining syrup over berries.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: jello cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend shortening, sugar, dry Jell-O, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll in 3/4-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine all ingredients together and pour over apples in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce with first 5 ingredients.
Put half the potatoes in greased 2-quart dish.
Cover with half the sauce and cheese; repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let brown.
Top with cheese.

title: bologna wedges
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and horseradish together until smooth and consistency to spread.
Spread between layers of bologna and cut into wedges.
Attractive and tasty.

title: chip dip
directions: 1st Layer:
Cook hamburg; add taco mix and refried beans.

title: hamburger helper
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off excess grease.
Boil macaroni in 4 quarts water with 1 teaspoon oil until tender.
Drain well.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat over low heat, stirring until well mixed.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice in oleo in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in lightly greased casserole. Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour (remove cover last 10 minutes).

title: ham and cheese delights
directions: Slice entire layer of rolls horizontally.
Mix the other 5 ingredients together and spread on rolls.
Place on top of the mixture the ham and cheese.
Replace tops of rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and cauliflower, cream of mushroom soup, 1 can of dried onions, 1 bag of cheese and cheese soup.
Mix in large mixing bowl; place in casserole dish.
Top with remaining bag of cheese and dried onions.
Make sure to cook broccoli and cauliflower before mixing with other ingredients.
Bake all ingredients in casserole dish until cheese is melted.

title: bacon fettucini
directions: Cook bacon in olive oil; remove and save.
Add onions, pepper and garlic.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Add spices except salt.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes more.
Add chicken broth; cook 5 more minutes. Transfer all to blender and puree; return to pan and add cream. Simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Add Blue cheese.
Melt over low heat. Cook fettucini in water with salt.
Drain and pour into bowl. Toss with sauce.
Top with bacon and Parmesan cheese.

title: double quick butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, 1/2 the flour and the salt.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add egg and oil.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth again.
Cover; let rise for 30 minutes, or until double.
Stir down and put in greased muffin cups 1/2 full.
Let rise to top.
Bake.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: choco-choco cake
directions: Stir together the pudding and cake mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan.
Pour a bag of chocolate chips on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix well and spread on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Cut peeled apples in thin slices.
Mix 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over apples and toss.
Blend flour, sugar, salt, eggs, oil, vanilla and orange juice for 1 minute on low, then 3 minutes on medium speed.
Add soda and powder.
Mix 1 minute.
In a greased tube pan, alternate layers of apples and batter (3 of batter and 2 of apples).
There is usually juice in the bottom of apple bowl and I pour this over top batter layer. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Freezes beautifully.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and add to all ingredients.
Blend well. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until done and lightly browned.

title: peanut butter rice krispie treats
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Melt peanut butter, margarine and peanut butter chips.
Stir until smooth.
Remove pan from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Stir until Rice Krispies are coated and then spread into the pan.
Refrigerate for one hour. Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: curry chicken
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Boil chicken in water to which 1 teaspoon of curry has been added, until tender.
Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Debone and cut chicken into pieces. Put chicken on top of rice.
Layer unthawed broccoli on top of chicken.

title: guacamole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine avocados, onions, lemon juice, salt, red pepper flakes, garlic powder and cilantro.
Using a fork or potato masher, mix and mash coarsely.
Add most of the tomatoes; stir well. Pour into serving bowl; garnish with remaining tomatoes and sprigs of cilantro.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: liver pate
directions: Boil livers and drain.
Grind.
Saute medium onion in liquid oil.
Drain oil and put into dish.
Add livers, grated eggs, salt and pepper to taste, nutmeg and mayonnaise for desired consistency.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together. Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually add the sugar, beating while adding. Add nuts and dates which have been cut into small pieces. Add dry ingredients, melted butter and vanilla. Pour into a greased 7 1/4 x 10 1/2 x 2 pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: leek and vermicelli soup
directions: Clean and slice the leeks, then saute in butter until soft. Keep the heat low and be careful not to let them brown.
Add red bell pepper and garlic; saute briefly.
Add the stock, pasta, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
To thicken the soup (optional), whisk together water and flour in a small bowl. Stir in half of flour/water mixture to thicken it slightly; use the rest to make it thicker.
Finally, stir in the milk and adjust seasonings to taste.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender, adding onion when vegetables are done.
Drain.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with cracker crumbs mixed with margarine.
Put in oven and bake at 325° until crumbs are brown.

title: s.o.s.
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain the grease.
Add handful of flour.
Stir in.
Pour in water.
Stir.
Pour in milk until desired consistency, slightly syrupy.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup walnuts.

title: smoothies
directions: Melt white chocolate and butterscotch coating.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons into small paper baking cups.

title: new yorkshire pudding
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Make well in center and stir in milk; beat in beaten egg whites then add water and 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Beat by hand until smooth and large bubbles rise to surface.
Set aside for 1 hour.

title: barbecue meat
directions: Cut beef into chunks.
Cook first 4 ingredients for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Shred into strips.
Add rest of ingredients and heat.
Serve over rice or use in sandwiches/buns.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed; pour into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: colline's cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Even better the next day.
This slaw will keep for several days.

title: beef hominy casserole
directions: Fry onion and bell pepper in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and brown; add drained hominy, seasonings, and tomato sauce. Place in greased baking dish.
Prepare sauce by combining melted butter, flour, milk and one-half of the grated cheese.
Cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over beef-hominy mixture and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding vinegar and vanilla last.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: quick and easy fruit cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir until dry particles are moistened.
Stir in fruit, dates, raisins and nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased 4 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan, which has been lined with brown paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dilly bacon corn muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, salt, bacon and dill.
In another bowl, combine milk, oil and egg.
Stir the liquid ingredients into dry.
Mix just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased pans and bake at 425° until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: microwave cabbage casserole
directions: Chop or shred cabbage and place in a 4-quart casserole dish. Add 1 cup of water and microwave for 15 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Drain cabbage, reserving juice.
Microwave 3 tablespoons of butter until melted.
Stir in flour; add milk and reserved water from cabbage.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes, or until thickened, stirring once a minute. In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer half of the cabbage, followed by half of the cheese, followed by half of the sauce.
Repeat.
Microwave the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter until melted.
Mix with the bread crumbs, sprinkling the crumb mixture on top of the cabbage casserole. Microwave for 8 to 10 minutes, turning once during cooking.

title: trout amandine
directions: Season cleaned trout with salt and pepper.
Coat lightly with flour and saute in hot oil until trout is golden on both sides. Drain oil from pan.
Add butter and brown almonds slightly.
Pour over trout.
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Skin and bone chicken; cut into 1-inch chunks.
Combine corn flake crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into butter; roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in single layer on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Bring potatoes and water to boil.
Add onion, celery, carrot, bouillon and a steeper with peppercorns and a bay leaf in it.
Simmer until potatoes are done. Remove steeper.
Add milk.
Serve hot.

title: lazy day fruit salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into deep dish.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Chill well.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain.
Combine ground beef and all above ingredients except pasta.
Simmer over low heat until onions and mushrooms are tender.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Finish by pouring stroganoff mixture over pasta.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Combine the beef broth, cornstarch, boiling water and pan drippings.
Boil a few minutes.
Make thick beef sandwiches from the sour dough French rolls or hard rolls.
Split and butter the rolls, put the meat in, wrap in foil, and heat for 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve dip in individual bowls, dunk sandwiches in dip.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken in a skillet in a small amount of oil.
Add sliced mushrooms and green onions.
Mix soup with water.
Add lemon juice and grated lemon peel.
Add to chicken; simmer until chicken is done, about 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serve with Rice-A-Roni chicken fried rice with almonds.

title: oreo delight
directions: In large mixing bowl, let ice cream soften slightly.
Fold in Cool Whip and coarsely crumbled Oreo cookies.
(Add instant coffee for a slight mocha taste.)
Pour into pan and return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: chicken livers
directions: Flour, salt and pepper livers.
Saute in 2 tablespoons Wesson oil.
Remove livers.
Wilt onion in skillet.
Add water and lemon pepper.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Add livers, sour cream and parsley.
Heat and serve over toast points or rice.

title: asparagus chicken casserole
directions: *If you need to thin soups, add chicken stock.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix half of cracker crumbs with ingredients; top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Place grated cheese on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jack's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni by directions.

Layer in a large baking dish 1 layer of macaroni, salt and pepper; dot with margarine, then 1 layer mellow Cheddar cheese and 1/2-inch American cheese, then 1 layer macaroni, salt and pepper; dot with margarine, then 1 layer mellow Cheddar cheese and 1/2-inch American cheese.
Cover top with the Cracker Barrel.
Beat by hand the eggs and 1 cup milk.
Pour around edges, then fill to the top with milk.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: grape-nut whip
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice in double boiler.
Cook over hot water until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together.
Add the other ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes. Bake in a Bundt pan.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles per directions, leaving slightly firm.
Using a long baking dish, pour sauce along bottom in a thin layer. Layer the noodles so bottom is completely covered.
Cut all cheeses into small pieces and sprinkle each type on noodles. Depending on preference, make this layer thick or thin.
The Ricotta cheese should be mixed with the two eggs and all spices added to it.
Spread this mixture on the noodles as well.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle each spice over sauce.
Repeat layers to the top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and noodles are tender.

title: marcella's chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream, chilies and chopped onion.

title: english meat and potato pie
directions: Use a 9-inch Pyrex dish; flour bottom of pie crust, which has been placed in a pie dish.
Spread meat first.
Slice potato rounds on meat.
Slice onion rounds on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cut pieces of butter on top of ingredients.
Add just a little water, so pie won't be dry.
Rotate same procedure again to fill dish.
Put remaining butter on top.
Place other pie shell on top, close as to finish pie off.
Cut slits in pie to let out steam.
When ready to eat, chili sauce or ketchup can be put on top of pie (optional).

title: clemon's chicken mosca
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, except add the chicken bouillon cube, a bay leaf, a dash of clove, a dash of cayenne, a splash of olive oil and anything else you might desire to the water.
Most recipes call for whole brown rice to be cooked for 45 minutes.
Cook it only 35 to 40 minutes.
It taste better and has a nuttier texture.
Once your rice is on, start the chicken wings.

title: different pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add, while continuing to beat, sugar and baking powder (mixed together) and flavoring.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all dry ingredients in sifter and sift in bowl.
Beat sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin filling to eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients from bowl.
Bake in 3 or 4 loaf pans at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes real good.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in 3-quart pot.
After coming to a boil, stir and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally adding extra water if needed.
Five minutes before finished, mix 1 tablespoon flour and 1 tablespoon water in a cup until all lumps dissolve.
Pour mixture into soup and stir well while pouring. Turn off burner.

title: cheese roll
directions: Cut cheese in strips and put in icebox before grinding.
Grind cheese, pecans and garlic.
Mix with cream cheese by hand.
Form into rolls, 1 to 1 1/2 inches thick.
Roll in chili powder.

title: rum balls
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat. Remove from heat, stir in sugar, rum, syrup and salt. Fold in wafers and nuts. Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in sugar. Place on cookie sheet and chill. Store in airtight container.

title: caramel-coconut squares
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Put into ungreased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine milk, butterscotch, coconut and vanilla; spread over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Mix all ingredients saving the Cool Whip for last.
Pour mixture into mold, individual cupcake liners or casserole dish before freezing.
Thaw for 15 minutes before serving.
Can be made 1 week in advance.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown. Drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, taco sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Heat to boiling.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown the ground meat. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the uncooked onion. Slice the potatoes and add, uncooked.
Place in layers in casserole dish and top with the mushroom soup.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: hershey's double chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top springs back when touched.
Cool completely in pan.
Spread mint cream layer on cake (recipe follows).
Chill.
Pour chocolate topping over dessert (recipe follows).
Cover and chill.

title: lentil soup(shonaba' addas)
directions: Place washed lentils and chopped onion in water and simmer, covered, for one hour.
Mix oil, flour, salt and spices in a bowl. Add 1/4 cup of soup to mixture and stir well.
Pour the mixture into the soup and let simmer until the lentils are well cooked. Add lemon juice and simmer five more minutes.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: mile-high biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, all at one time.
Stir with fork to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead lightly 15 times.
Roll to 1-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In food processor, chop onion and jalapeno pepper.
Add sugar, chili powder, salt and Cheddar.
Coat large, cast-iron frypan with bacon grease.
Pour in all mixed ingredients and bake at 375° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: wacky mac pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed (do not over cook).
Drain and add mayonnaise and dressing.
Toss well.
Add vegetables, salt, pepper and cheese.
Toss and refrigerate.
Can be done ahead as flavors blend over time.
Can also add more mayo or dressing if needed.

title: barbecue short ribs
directions: Brown ribs in the oil over medium heat.
Add the onion, water, ketchup, vinegar, curry powder, chili powder, dry mustard and salt.
Cover. Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Add the potatoes, carrots and another cup of water. Cover and simmer about 1/2 to 1 hour until meat is tender.

title: hershey cake(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add melted Hershey bars and blend.
Add sifted dry ingredients with buttermilk, beating well after each addition. Add Hershey's syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not invert while cooling!

title: six-in-one cookies(makes 6 flavors, 18 dozen, from 1 batch)
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugars.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla, oil and grated zucchini.

Mix together. Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Mix the zucchini mixture and flour mixture together by hand. Add chopped nuts. Grease and flour 3 large bread tins. Fill each tin 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool 15 minutes and remove bread from tins.

title: candle stick salad
directions: Place each lettuce leaf on individual salad plate.
Put a slice of pineapple on each leaf.
Peel and cut bananas in half crosswise.
Place a half banana in each pineapple ring, cut side down.
You may have to trim the banana a bit to make it stand upright in the pineapple ring.
Put a tablespoon of mayonnaise and a cherry on top of each banana half.
Serves 4.

title: bobbye lou's fudge
directions: Cook to soft, firm ball.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool before cutting.

title: turtle cake
directions: Blend cake mix, butter and 1 cup milk. Spread half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sugar free brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over low heat.
Add sweetener, vanilla and eggs; stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Press in cake or jelly roll pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 270°.
Cool.
Mix melted chocolate and peanut butter together.
Spread over baked layer.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat 1 cup sugar, brown sugar, milk, flour and butter until dissolved; let cool.
Beat 1 whole egg, 3 egg yolks and vanilla. Add to cooled vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn oven down to 250° until firm on edge (10 minutes).
Beat whites, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla for meringue.
Top and brown.

title: salmon dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with potato chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish cake
directions: Cook together the first 7 ingredients on top of stove.
Bring to a boil and cool. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 hours.
It is important that it bake the 2 hours.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat well egg whites.
Add sugar slowly.
Continue beating until mixture stands in firm peaks.
Fold into egg mixture Ritz crackers, rolled fine and walnuts, cut fine.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool; spread chocolate whipped cream, leaving edge bare.
Keep in fridge until ready to serve.

title: better-than-best fried ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and corn flakes together.
Take a scoop (rounded) of vanilla ice cream and roll it in the mixture.
Beat eggs.
Dip the ice cream in the eggs.
Roll in the corn flake mixture for a second time.
Deep fry in hot grease for 15 seconds. Put in an ice cream sundae glass and top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: sesame chicken
directions: First, in a medium bowl, mix together the broth, parsley, onion, soy sauce, oil and ginger.
Add chicken; toss until well coated.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Drain chicken.
Place chicken on skewers.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Place on broil pan; broil 4 inches from heat for 3 minutes.
Turn over and broil for 3 to 5 minutes, until done.

title: buns
directions: Pour milk into bowl with sugar.
When lukewarm, add yeast in water.
Stir in enough flour to make pancake batter texture. This is called the "sponge".
Let stand until bubbly, about 1/2 hour in warm place.
Then mix in rest of ingredients and set with flour.
Leave it sticky.
Let rise 1 hour in warm place.
Punch down and let rise 1 more hour.
Form into buns and put in greased pan.
Let rise, then bake.
Butter tops when done.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Cover a cookie tin with aluminum foil.
Cut the broilers (if using) into quarters.
Season the oil with Lawry's salt (can use regular pepper), pepper, paprika and garlic.
Using a pastry brush, apply the seasoned oil to the chicken pieces; roll them in the corn flake crumbs.
Place the chicken pieces in shallow pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in double boiler top. Slowly stir in water.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick enough to mound slightly when dropped from spoon.
Cover, cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolk and 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend a little hot mixture into egg yolks.
Stir all remaining hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from boiling water.
Gently stir in margarine, lemon rind and juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Turn into pastry shell.
Beat egg after each addition.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread some meringue around edge of filling, first touching crust all around then fill in center.
Bake in 350° moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes, or until meringue is lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Total cooking time:
4 minutes, 30 seconds.

title: real chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; beating well after each addition.
Mix in vanilla and almond extracts.
Gradually add in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack or serving plate to cool.
Top with Chocolate Glaze.

title: party mix
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels, potatoes, and nuts in large roasting pan.
Combine oil, brown sugar, Worcestershire, and garlic salt.
Pour over first set of ingredients and toss to coat. Bake in 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together the sausage, cheese and biscuit mix. Shape into small balls and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese rice krispies
directions: Mix margarine and cheese; add flour and pepper.
Mix well. Add Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese hearts
directions: Line six 1/2 cup or eight 1/3 cup heart shape or other molds with damp cheesecloth squares, allowing the cheesecloth to hang over edges.

title: blue strawberry shake
directions: Combine fruit and juice in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice slowly until desired thickness.
Serves 6.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream brown sugar, white
sugar,
shortening,
vanilla and eggs. Add flour and oatmeal.
Pour into 11
x
7-inch pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Melt
chocolate and spread over bars. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Press Krispies in pan.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Beat eggs. Add soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish. Add cooked broccoli, cheese and cooked rice.
Stir well.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes or microwave 20 minutes covered.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken, potatoes and vegetables in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine soup, water, broth, gravy and pepper in bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture. Combine biscuit mix, milk and butter; stir until smooth.
Pour biscuit mixture on top of other ingredients.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces and brown.
Drain can of mushrooms.
Place steak in slow cooker.
Mix soup mix, water, mushroom soup and mushrooms and add to slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Excellent when served with mashed potatoes.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Spread mixture evenly over cooled crust.
Spread with chilled blueberries on top.
You may use different fruits of your choice.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 2 loaf pans at 350°.

title: crystal light shake
directions: Mix Crystal Light as directed on package.
Pour 6 to 8 ounces Crystal Light lemonade into blender.
Add Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplement and Sweet 'N Low.
Blend well.
Add ice gradually and blend until smooth.

title: crock-pot cabbage soup
directions: Place browned meat in bottom of crock-pot.
Layer prepared vegetables on top.
Pour in juice.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours on high. If you use rice, add during last hour of cooking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan scrolls
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and beat until light. Add eggs; blend well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and mix.
Drop by scant teaspoonful 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet and with back of spoon, press thin as possible.
Bake at 352° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll at once over handle of spoon as they harden rapidly.
Will make 3 dozen.

title: fried turkey
directions: You will need a deep fryer or fish cooker and a clip-on thermometer.

title: terry's moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and add hot coffee.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tea punch
directions: Cover tea bags with about 4 cups water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cover and let set 10 minutes.
Strain into gallon container. Add sugar, stir very well, then add frozen orange juice and frozen lemonade, stir until dissolved.
Finish filling with cold water to make a gallon.
Refrigerate.
This is a very refreshing beverage!

title: spirited cider
directions: Simmer all together except brandy.
Add brandy just before serving.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix hominy, chilies and soup; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover with crumbs and brown.

title: shrimp-pasta sauce
directions: Saute garlic and oregano in oil.
Add shrimp and saute till done.
Add sauce and wine; serve over your favorite pasta.

title: berry patch coffee cake(yield: 1 coffee cake)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine softened cream cheese, margarine and sugar; mixing until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dot with preserves. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, eggs, salt, pepper, soup mix, milk and crumbs.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Combine butter, flour, brown sugar, egg and vanilla to make dough.
Spread on 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Spread with peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake for 6 to 8 more minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add oil slowly, then stir in poppy seed.
Makes 1 quart.

title: skinny lasagna(zucchini lasagna bake)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute sausage lightly; place in bottom of deep casserole.
Cook zucchini and onion in frypan with butter until tender, but not brown.
Remove from heat and toss 4 tablespoons flour with zucchini mixture.
In medium bowl, mix cottage cheese, grated cheese, eggs, salt and 1 tablespoon flour. Spoon evenly over zucchini mixture; spread half of tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 2 minutes more.
Serve while hot.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Cook for 30 minutes and stir until Grape-Nuts settle at bottom of pan, then cook another 30 minutes.
Place in baking dish in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: special green bean au gratin
directions: Cook beans in bacon drippings.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Remove from heat.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend into cheese mixture.
Heat until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat and gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture thickens.
Cook an additional 2 or 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
When beans are tender, draining if necessary, add to sauce. Toss beans gently until well coated with sauce.

title: lime pear jello salad
directions: Put jello in boiling water. Add cream cheese and dissolve. Add juice of pears; mix. Place in refrigerator and let partially congeal.
Remove and beat.
Add mashed pears, nuts and Dream Whip. Blender may be used.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chicken-rice casserole
directions: Line oblong casserole dish with aluminum foil (for easy cleanup).
Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Turn chicken over. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes more until chicken is done.

title: jake's "kiss" cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together sugar, Crisco and peanut butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except kisses.
Spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cookies are taken out of oven, push in a kiss.
Let cool so kisses can set again. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: frosty fruit shake
directions: Combine all ingredients except yogurt in blender; process until smooth.
Add yogurt and process until blended.
Contains 135 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: peanut butter cookies(double batch)
directions: Cream butters; beat in sugars, then eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add extra flour if needed to make mixture stiff enough to drop cookies.
Arrange by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet; press flat with floured fork. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: crock-pot cheese and potato casserole
directions: Combine partially thawed hash browns, soup, milk and half the onion rings.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Add salt and pepper. Cover and cook on low 8 to 9 hours or 3 hours on high.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings over the top before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Add bread until it's pretty thick.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: high protein pancakes
directions: To flour, add powdered milk; blend in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop from tablespoon onto hot griddle.
Turn when bubbles form on top. Serve with butter and syrup or fruit topping.

title: pink salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O
over the Cool Whip. Add cottage cheese. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat egg in another small bowl. In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil, salt and milk. Stir until lukewarm, then add yeast and egg.
Add flour until dough is soft, but not sticky.
Knead on floured board.
Place in washed, oiled bowl and let rise 1 to 1 1/2
hours in a warm place.
Turn out on board and cut into 32 pieces.

title: royal zucchini
directions: Saute meat and onions in oil until brown; drain.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, tomatoes and green peppers.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend cheese, seasonings and zucchini in.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve.

title: quick quesadillas
directions: Place 1 flour tortilla on a plate or paper towel.
Spread grated cheese and optional ingredient(s) on tortilla.
Cover with second tortilla.
Place a paper towel on top and put into microwave.
Heat on High for 30 seconds.
Pull out and remove paper towel.
Cut in half and enjoy.
Serves 1.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Fold in soy mayonnaise.
Stir and chill.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix together cherry jello, lime jello and crushed pineapple. Put on stove and cook until boiling.
Take off stove and add Coke and nuts to mixture.
Stir in pan well; pour in bowl and refrigerate.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add rice, then remaining ingredients. Cook about 1/2 hour on low heat.

title: crabmeat-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, dry and remove the stems of the mushrooms.
Melt the butter in a skillet; saute the mushroom caps, hollow side up, for 3 minutes.
Transfer to a buttered shallow baking dish.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until soft peaks form. Fold yolks into whites.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; fold into egg mixture.

title: mary turvey's banana bread
directions: Bake slow for 1 hour at 300°.
Can divide evenly between 2 loaf pans and bake at 300° for approximately 45 minutes or until done.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate and they're ready to eat in 24 hours.
Keep cool in refrigerator.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Slice apples into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix cinnamon and chopped nuts over sliced apples.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell and bake about 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: creamy treat punch
directions: Combine 1 can of the following undiluted frozen concentrates: orange juice, lemonade and limeade.
Add one tray ice cubes and 46 ounce can of pineapple juice.
Mix and chill.
One hour before serving, add 1 quart peppermint ice cream.
Blend with mixer. Thaw 1 package strawberries (or use fresh) and add to juice mixture.
Add 1 quart well chilled ginger ale and serve immediately.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Drop batter in very small muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350 degrees.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into Pyrex dish.

title: cocktail dogs
directions: Boil wieners.
Mix barbecue sauce, syrup, sugar and cinnamon. Add wieners.
Transfer to crock-pot or slow cooker; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together onion, soup, sour cream, margarine, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator. Remove chicken and coat each piece with bread crumbs.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: orange dessert
directions: Heat ginger ale and orange juice and put over marshmallows; cool.
Mix Cool Whip and marshmallows together.
Break up cake in bite size pieces.
Place cake in bottom of pan, a layer at a time. After layer of cake, spread marshmallow mixture.
Repeat until all is used.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top and place in refrigerator overnight or until firm.

title: sneaky pete
directions: Stir all ingredients together in large container and freeze; drink will be slushy.
Great for party or New Year's Eve, but keep away from children.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers or potato chips.

title: jello dessert
directions: Follow pkg directions to make jello.
Add a can of pie filling & chill. Use any combination of jello & filling; top with whipped cream & serve.

title: dressing
directions: Cook 1 hour at 350° in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: baked tuna balls
directions: Combine tuna, egg, bread crumbs, mayonnaise, onion, parsley, mustard and poultry seasoning.
Mix well.
Shape into 40 balls. Roll in corn flakes.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serve on cocktail picks.

title: old english toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar and nuts and heat slowly to boiling. Boil to 300°, stirring constantly while candy cooks.
Pour out on greased baking sheet and spread flat.
Melt Hershey bar to spread over cooked mixture on cookie sheet.
Add additional nuts on top, if desired.
When hardened, crack with knife and let set one week.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Garnish with maraschino cherries on top for color.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cook dried apricots in 1 cup water.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg, salt and buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder; add nuts.
Mix with batter.
Fold in apricots.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in large loaf pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine. Pour milk evenly over crumbs and top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.
If desired, melt 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips with 1 1/2 teaspoons shortening.
Drizzle evenly.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: carolyn's layered chicken casserole
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Layer chicken on bottom.
Layer your favorite cheese.
Layer prepared stuffing.
Pour soup and water mixture on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook stewing hen in crock pot or regular pot

for 7 to 8 hours. Salt and pepper to taste and cover the hen with water. Cook on low heat. To make your dumplings mix flour, salt and enough cold water to make a soft dough. Cover and set in refrigerator for two hours. Take out and put on floured surface. Work more flour in to make a stiff dough. Divide into 5 parts, roll out thin and cut into strips. Place wax paper on cookie sheet and lay strips on cookie sheet side by side. Repeat layers on wax paper until all dough has been used. Cover and freeze overnight. When ready to cook dumplings remove the hen parts from the broth. Transfer broth to a large pot and bring broth to a boil. Break frozen strips of dough and drop into broth until you have enough dumplings. Turn heat down, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix all the ingredients together.
(You can melt the butter to make it easier.)
Bake for 60 to 75 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 6 hours before serving. Freezes very well.

title: "real trooper cupcakes"
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder, soda and cocoa, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add coffee.
Fill greased (or paper lined) cupcake pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
These are very light, moist and rich brown and a delicious treat.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: hungry jack coffee cake
directions: Dip each biscuit in melted butter, then in sugar and cinnamon, then in nuts and coconut.
Stack them on end in tube pan. Put excess mixture on top of coffee cake.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: potato balls
directions: Mix well and roll in flour. Drop the balls in boiling water, they are finished when they rise to the top.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Pour 1/2 milk over baked crust. Sprinkle nuts over milk and pour remaining milk over nuts.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Add topping and continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: pastasciutta(pronounced pastashuta; old italian recipe)
directions: Cut up onion; simmer with butter in pan until onion is tender. Add the can of tomatoes (cut up) and 1 can water, then add the tomato paste.
Stir and simmer on low heat for about 30 minutes. (Add meat if desired.)
Add cooked noodles; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers,
peppers
and onions.	Pack into jars. Heat and cook sugar,
vinegar
and spices for 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers, peppers and onions in jars, and seal.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add all ingredients, using 1/2 of the pecans. Mix well and form into ball. Roll in remaining nuts.

title: holly's mom's crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine in saucepan the butter and flour.
Heat until butter has melted.
Add cream and milk.
Cook until dissolved.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add extract.
Spray tube pan generously with Pam.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add beans.
Fry.
Blend tomatoes and pepper.
Add to meat mixture.
Mix. Add Spanish rice.
Mix. Using large baking dish, layer meat mixture, Doritos and cheese alternately.
Finish with cheese on top.
Heat in oven until melted.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: tony tiger bites
directions: Microwave:
In a 4-quart bowl, melt butter and marshmallows together on High for 3 minutes, stirring halfway through.

title: mexican squash
directions: Saute the diced squash and onion in oil until tender.
Add the milk and chilies; remove from fire.
Add the cheese.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken breast, saving 2 cups of broth for later.
Saute carrots, celery and onion in butter for 4 to 5 minutes.
Brown flour for about 1 minute.
Combine all ingredients and place in ovenproof dish.
Top with pie crust and bake at 400° until crust has browned.

title: noisemaker appetizers
directions: Place wonton wrapper on a work surface with one corner facing you:
roll into a cone.
Cut the open end with a sharp scissors until edge is even.
Place a 1 inch foil ball in opening.
Place seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining wonton wrappers.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
In a small bowl combine the butter, 1/2 tsp. dill and garlic salt.
Brush over horns.
Remove to a wire rack and cool completely.
Remove foil balls.
In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add the sour cream, lemon juice and dill.
Mix well. Fold in the crab.
Transfer to a pastry or plastic bag (with the corner cut).
Pipe in to cooled horns.
Yield 2 dozen.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Beat cream cheese in mixer.
Add cake mix, using their directions except omit oil.
Mix sugar, spices and flour.
Pour half cake dough into stem pan that has been oiled and floured. Add sugar mixture in layer.
Add rest of cake dough.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Toss zucchini and onion over medium heat in butter for 10 minutes.
Add seasonings and cook 2 more minutes.
In large bowl, mix eggs, cheese and veggies with seasonings.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with unbaked crescent rolls.
Pour veggie mix on top of crescent rolls and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: butter beans
directions: Dice bacon and fry with onion until done.
Don't drain fat off bacon and onions as this adds a lot of flavor.
Place beans in a large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thickened, about 1 hour, on low heat.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Combine juices.
Bring to a boil 1/2 cup of combined juices.
Dissolve gelatin in hot juice. Add cola, allow to congeal slightly.
Add fruit and nuts.
Crumble cheese and sprinkle in bottom of salad mold.
Pour gelatin mixture into mold.
Chill.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage, breaking it into bits as you cook it.
Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish; add sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and pop in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
This is an easy and great breakfast.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: In covered casserole dish, mix all ingredients well.
Layer diced bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage pecan dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and spices in butter.
Cook sausage.
Mix sausage, corn bread, pecans and onion-celery mixture together. Use chicken broth to add moisture.
You may bake at 350°
until brown or use as a stuffing for turkey.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in casserole dish.

title: freezer dessert
directions: Mix cereal, oleo or butter, sugar and coconut together.
Line an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with ice cream and put in freezer until set.
Cut into servings and top with cherry pie filling (or other pie mix).
Makes 8 servings.
May double for larger groups.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix sliced or chopped artichokes with mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Place in low baking dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together and add to mixture flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.

title: wash day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Pour batter in casserole dish.
Add peaches or other fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and combine with other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole and bake in 350° oven until done.
Season with your choice of curry powder, garlic powder, parsley, sage, etc.

title: fettuccine with spinach cheese sauce
directions: Squeeze out water from spinach.
Mince garlic; add parsley. Add minced walnuts, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper (can use processor to do).
Add spinach and oil to form a puree.

title: cake-n-bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll out and cut into desired shapes. Decorate and bake at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: pineapple-orange "marmalade"
directions: Combine the gelatin with the defrosted orange juice in a saucepan.
Wait until the gelatin is softened, then add all the other ingredients except the sugar substitute.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes, then stir in the sweetener.
Stir in jars in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups, 15 calories per tablespoon.

title: jewel fruit cake
directions: Line pans with brown paper and grease.
Mix all ingredients; pour into pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, then bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple, marshmallows, pears, white grapes, cherries, nuts, peaches and bananas.
Moisten with salad dressing. Arrange on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with maraschino.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch cake pan with cooking spray.
Spread 1/2 jar of peanuts in bottom of pan.
In bowl, microwave until just blended the Eagle Brand milk, peanut butter chips and oleo.
Stir, then add marshmallows and microwave until melted.
Stir well and pour over nuts in cake pan.
Spread rest of nuts on top and refrigerate until it sets.
Keep refrigerated.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs and add vanilla. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Combine 1 cup flour and spices; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and bourbon.
Beat well after each addition.
Coat fruit with 1/2 cup flour; stir fruit and nuts into batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt and pepper until tender. Remove and debone.
Use broth for cooking dumplings in.

title: no bake lemon cheesecake
directions: Prepare a graham cracker or vanilla cookie crust in a 9-inch pie pan; cool.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in saltwater until fork-tender; drain and cool.
When cool, mix.
Make marinade with remaining liquid, beating well (blender or beater).
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate.
Can be prepared several days in advance and kept in the refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar; beat in eggs.
Beat well; add zucchini. Mix together flour and cinnamon.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Beat thoroughly; pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cocoa puff cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Boil until blended.
Add peanut butter; stir well.
Add Cocoa Puffs.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on wax paper.

title: saucy potatoes for company
directions: Cook potatoes, in boiling water to cover, 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients.
Blend
together
remaining ingredients
and
fold
into dry ingredients just until mixed. Do not stir too much.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: white wedding punch
directions: Mix juices together.
When ready to serve, put juices in punch bowl.
Add scoops of ice cream; pour in ginger ale.
Stir lightly.
Makes 30 servings.

title: glazed carrots with fine herbs
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of salted water until tender and water has boiled away.
Add butter and sugar; cook, turning often, until carrots are evenly cooked and well glazed.
Sprinkle carrots lightly with chopped chives, tarragon, basil and salt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: biscuit pizzas
directions: Place biscuits on baking sheet and press out with hand.
Cover with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with toppings of your choice and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake according to biscuit directions.

title: recipe for education
directions: Blend the thinking and the dreams.
Add the years and beat until creamy.
Sift persistence and ability together and add alternately with cooperation to the first mixture.
Add borrowing books, lectures, teachers, health and plans.
Fold in the years of youth, beaten stiff.
Bake in any moderately good college or university.
Time in college: four or more years, depending on how you like your finished product.
Temperature:
plenty hot. Servings will last for life.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Cook milk in a saucepan over low heat until hot.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy; gradually add sugar and salt, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix after each addition.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan; let cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: no-fat cucumber cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in onion and cucumber.
Place in a covered container and chill for 1 hour prior to serving.
Serve with fresh veggies or low-fat crackers.

title: cracker crumb pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1 cup sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans and cracker crumbs.
Put into well-greased pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°. When cool, beat 1 cup of whipping cream, adding 1/2 cup of sugar. Remove from mixer and stir in 2 or 3 tablespoons of crushed pineapple.
Spread this whipped cream mixture over cooled crust and sprinkle with coconut.
This must be refrigerated and is actually better made the day before you plan to eat it.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add to broccoli.
Add soup, milk, Cheez Whiz, rice and salt and pepper to suit taste.
Place mixture in baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with French fried onion rings and bake another 10 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix milk and vinegar to sour; add oil, then add flour mixture.
Roll out and cut to 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: food for birds
directions: Heat the fats and oils.
Add peanut butter and seed and mix well.
Pour into the clean cans and let cool.
Unmold.
Put cakes on bird feeder or window ledge or tie in a tree.

title: peach crunch
directions: Place peaches in baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix flour, sugar and egg until lumpy.
Spread this mixture over peaches.
Pour melted butter over top of this.
Bake at 375° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange crush
directions: Add half the cranberries and half the orange pieces to food processor.
Turn on and off rapidly, until mixture is evenly chopped.
Transfer to a bowl.
Repeat with remaining cranberries and orange pieces.
Add sugar to taste.
Makes 3 cups.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or freezer.
Very good with turkey and dressing.

title: pink salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into patties.
Heat electric skillet.
In 1 cup cooking oil, fry patties until brown and crispy.
Brown both sides.
Makes 7 to 8 patties.

title: overnight easy omelet
directions: Butter bread.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, buttered side up. Beat together the next 3 ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Grate Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and cook in water with desired seasonings until tender.
After chicken is done, debone and set aside.
Save 1 1/2 quarts of broth.
Chop onions.
Add bell peppers and saute in 1 1/2 sticks oleo until tender.
Add Ro-Tel, english peas (drained) and mushrooms (drained).
Cook pasta in 1 1/2 quarts of broth until tender.
Add cheese and chopped chicken to all other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and cook in 350 degree oven until bubbly hot.
This can also be placed in a crockpot and cooked on low for a couple of hours.
Be sure to watch it, and stir frequently so that it doesn't stick to the crockpot.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Roll graham crackers to crumbs.
Take out 1/2 cup and set aside.
Put remaining crumbs in mixing bowl and add sugar, cinnamon, and melted butter.
Mix well and line the well-buttered pans with the crumbs.
Can be made in a 9 inch square cake pan or two pie tins.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour or cornstarch and eggs.
Add milk; cook until thick.
Add vanilla, coconut and oleo.

title: corn casserole
directions: Select	nice, clean corn and cut off both ends, without exposing
the kernels.
Do not remove silks before microwaving as they add sweetness to the corn.
Remove only the outer dry husks. Open
the
tips
of
corn, just enough to let the cold water trickle
in.
Let
set
about 5 minutes, then shake out excess water.
Microwave
on
High,
3 corns for about 7 to 8 minutes, or if just one corn, 3 minutes.
Allow to set without opening the door for a few moments.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll out real thin.
Cut with cutters.
Bake at 350°.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain water from green and yellow beans.
Wash kidney beans. Mix sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves, heating a little helps.
Cool and add oil; pour over beans and mix well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, cinnamon and water.
Rub together flour, sugar and butter until crumbly and drop mixture over apples. Bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with cream.
This makes six servings.

title: a real pound cake
directions: Sift the soda and the cream of tartar into the flour. Rub the butter and sugar to a cream.
Add one-quarter of the whites and yolks, next the flour and then the milk.
Beat in the remaining yolks and mix in the remaining whites in that order.
Have a not too easy oven ready (325°) and bake 1 1/4 hours.
Test for doneness.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight or until very firm.
Cut into serving pieces. Dip in flour and brown in skillet using Crisco or oil.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/2 can mushroom soup and 1/2 can beef gravy.
Lay meat in soup and gravy.
Top with 1/2 can soup and 1/2 can gravy. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
This freezes well.

title: caramel butter frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for about 1 minute or until slightly thick. Cool slightly.
Add milk and beat until smooth with electric mixer.
Beat in confectioners sugar until spreading consistency. (Add more milk if too thick or more sugar if too thin.)

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into 1-inch balls.

title: chicken-italian dressing bake
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and salt in a plastic bag.
Shake to mix.
Dip chicken in salad dressing.
Place 1 piece of chicken in bag; shake to coat.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken. Place in a lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Spray chicken with cooking spray; bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mocha oatmeal cake
directions: Combine Postum and boiling water; pour over oats.
Stir, cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat shortening and vanilla and oat mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or angel food pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Combine the ground beef, egg, chili sauce, chopped onion, salt and pepper with 1 cup cheese cracker crumbs.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into tiny meatballs and roll in the remaining 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 10 minutes; peel.
Cut them in half and remove yolks.
Mix yolks with mustard and mayonnaise.
Fill eggs with the yolk mixture and serve.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Optional: A 6 ounce package of chocolate chips can be added.

title: uncle jack's spaghetti sauce
directions: Blend ingredients in blender; don't whip.
Pour over 1 pound extra lean, browned ground beef.
Simmer on low for 10 minutes. Serve over drained spaghetti.
Can be used over fried zucchini or squash and chopped onion, covered with cheese and baked.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a 3-quart oblong dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and meat.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: old berliner frankfurter skillet
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon five minutes.
Add onion and cook until it is tender.
Add broth , vinegar, sugar, pickling spice, salt and pepper.
Bring to a simmer, add cabbage, cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slash franks crosswise six or seven times, about 1/4 inch deep.
Place them over cooked cabbage.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes more.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Alternately add milk and flour, mixing well. Add vanilla. Pour into 3 layer pans. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: lime chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir together cake flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg yolks, oil, water, lime juice and rind. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. When all ingredients are mixed well, pour into loaf pan (ungreased). Bake for 55 to 65 minutes at 350°.

title: confederate sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs and margarine.
Pour into casserole.

title: sheila's irish soda bread
directions: Cut 1/4 lb. margarine into the above mixture. Add 2 Tbsp. caraway seeds, 1 c. raisins (loosely packed). Add 1 1/2 c. buttermilk. Stir until all moistened. Grease and flour a heavy pan or 10 inch cast iron skillet. Cut a cross into dough, bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. After about 30 minutes in oven, rub a stick of margarine over the top and around the sides of pan.

title: juju's frozen dessert
