directions: Mix well all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Cover with Reynolds Wrap. Put into freezer for at least 2 hours. When ready to serve, take out of freezer, allowing to thaw slightly. Enjoy a cool treat.

title: chocolate covered peanut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter and powdered sugar; mix well. Add cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Roll in small balls. Refrigerate 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
When well chilled, melt the chocolate pieces and paraffin wax together in a double boiler. Dip peanut balls in hot, melted chocolate, using toothpicks to dip with.
Refrigerate.

title: coriander rosti
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork and bake at 400°
for 40 minutes, or until softened, but not cooked through.
Peel and finely chop onions until soft without browning (5 to 7 minutes).
When potatoes are cool, peel and grate coarsely.
Add cooked onions and seasonings.
Spoon mixture into 16 rough mounds on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400°
for 40 minutes, or until crisp and golden.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Stew large fryer hen with bay leaves.
When tender, cool and debone.
Cook 8 ounces spaghetti.
Saute celery, onion and garlic in margarine.
Add mushrooms, undrained Ro-Tel, tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Grate 1/2 pound cheese; mix all together. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This casserole freezes well.

title: easy layered mexican casserole
directions: In a 10 x 10-inch casserole dish, line ground beef.
Layer corn tortillas, Ranch Style beans, grated cheese, tortillas, cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Take a knife and poke in several places.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with favorite salad and warm buttermilk flour tortillas.

title: foolproof dinner rolls
directions: Mix eggs, yeast mixture and shortening mixture.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth mixture develops.
Place dough in oiled pan and cover with cloth.
Set in warm place to rise, about 2 hours.
Cut dough in half and roll out on floured board to 1-inch thickness and cut in pie shapes.
Roll up from large end to point and curve into crescent shape.
Cover with dry cloth and set aside in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes and lightly brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk, sugar, butter and vanilla in a pot until butter melts.
Cube slices of bread and lay in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Pour the mixture over bread.
Beat eggs and cinnamon over the bread mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, butter and Crisco as if for pie crust.
In another bowl, mix sugar, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, baking powder and cream of tartar; mix well.
Combine the two mixtures until smooth.
Chill in fridge at least one hour.

title: delicious (easy) fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients into a batter.
Pour over 2 cups of fruit (peaches, apple, cherry).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend in all ingredients together.
Be sure to use self-rising flour.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Insert a knife to see if it's firm.
Requires no pie shell.
Very good.

title: red cinnamon jelly
directions: Sterilize jelly jars.
Combine water, sugar and candies.
Boil slowly for 30 minutes to dissolve candies.
Add Certo.
Boil for 1 minute.
Skim until clear.
Fill jelly jars.
Seal with 1/4-inch of melted paraffin.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (chill). Shape into balls. Place Spinach Balls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls(eastern european)
directions: Discard outside leaves of cabbage.
In rolling boil, put carefully separated whole leaves of cabbage in water.
Boil a few minutes.
Drain.
Put aside to cool.
Cook hamburger, onion and garlic together.
Parboil rice to soft without cover.
Add pepper, parsley, paprika and rosemary to hamburger.
Stuff cabbage with this mixture.
Fold and secure with toothpicks.
Put in baking pan and cover with sauerkraut and whole tomatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together and shape as a loaf or ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: quick chow mein
directions: Let frozen veggies thaw in pan and add 1 cup water.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce to your own taste.
Salt to your taste. Thicken with cornstarch and serve over noodles or cooked rice.

title: rolled oat clusters
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Bring to full boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add oats; mix well.
Cool mixture until it holds shape.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper. Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all of the above in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cup melted butter and 1 to 2 cups crushed corn flakes.	Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade stuffing
directions: Mix bread, onions, carrots, celery, sage, salt and pepper with margarine and chicken broth.
Put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken bake
directions: Place stuffing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; break up chicken into small pieces and layer chicken, broccoli and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whiskey nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. Cream butter and remaining sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, 1/3 cup at a time, alternating with whiskey. Mix well. Stir in vanilla, almond extract and pecans. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 3 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. (I have done 1 Bundt and 1 loaf pan.) Bake for 1 hour. Freezes well. (Good for Christmas.)

title: red pop punch
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Add Faygo red pop - half and half over frozen slush.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box. Add 1/2 stick oleo and small cream cheese. Stir until melted and well mixed. Pour into casserole dish. Mix herb bread crumbs and 1/2 stick oleo. Crumble on top of spinach mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt van's russian baked chicken
directions: Cut an "X" in chicken breasts; place in baking dish, meaty side up.
Mix onion soup, red Russian dressing and peach preserves. Pour over chicken breasts and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice using sauce as gravy.

title: crisfield crab-burgers
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Mix crabmeat, green pepper, celery, onion, mayonnaise and cheese cubes in a bowl.
Add Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, salt and lemon and pepper seasoning.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken; put a little salt in to season.
When real tender, take off the bone.
Take the large pan that you are going to cook your dressing in and crumble your crackers up, putting them into pan.
Add the chicken, cream of chicken soup, celery soup, cream of mushroom soup, pimientos, onion and eggs.
Pour stock juice over ingredients.
Mix well; may add a little pepper. (Be careful not to over salt, as your crackers are already salted.)
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: Wash orange roughy; pat dry with paper towel.
Season the fish with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Coat the fish with mayonnaise.
Arrange the fish on a baking dish. Spread the bell pepper and dill on top of the arranged fish. Bake for 20 minutes or until opaque color of fish appears at 350°. Serve hot with steamed rice.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour coconut cream and Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let set for 2 hours. Frost with Cool Whip, coconut and chopped pecans mixed together.

title: sour cherry pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over remainder of ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator 4 to 6 weeks.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar and syrup over low heat, stirring constantly, until soft ball forms.
Add butter and coconut flavoring; stir in, but do not beat.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well and form balls.

title: spicy roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces.
Combine rice and raisins; place near center of each piece of meat.
Roll up, tuck ends in, fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in shortening in skillet, pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken ala can can
directions: Cut up chicken into small pieces.
Mix first 4 ingredients in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbling.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix well. Add orange juice, pineapple and nuts.
Stir and pour into a mold sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm and serve.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook cleaned carrots in salted water until tender.
Cool and drain.
Add sliced onions and green pepper.
Cover with sauce made with rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and pour over vegetables.

title: catch of sea chowder
directions: In saucepan, brown salt pork and remove it; in drippings, cook onion, celery and carrots until tender.
Add salt pork and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes or until fish is tender, stirring frequently.

title: party chicken casserole
directions: Put dried beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Wrap each chicken breast half in a strip of bacon.
Place on dried beef.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken (no salt or pepper needed).
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing well. Pinch off a walnut-sized piece of dough.
Roll in floured hands to make a smooth ball.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Use thumb to make depression in center of cookie and fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (until jelly is bubbly, but don't let edges get too brown).
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: peach butterscotch crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients together thoroughly.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until the consistency of coarse meal.
Butter a 1-quart baking dish. Arrange peaches and spread crumb mixture over the top.
Bake about 10 minutes and reduce oven heat to 325°, baking another 30 minutes or until fruit is soft.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: kaju murgh kari-curried chicken with cashews(origin:  india and pakistan)
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
For curry, pieces should not be large, so separate drumsticks from thighs, wings from breasts and cut breasts into four.
If large, the thighs and drumsticks can be chopped in halves using a heavy cleaver and cutting through the bone.
The smaller pieces of chicken, the better the spices can penetrate.

title: sweet-and-sour red cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, combine drippings or oil, brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Cook for 2-3 minutes or until hot, stirring occasionally.
Add cabbage; cover and cook for 10 minutes over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add apples and cook uncovered for about 10 minutes more or until tender. Yield 6-8 servings.
If cooking for two:
Cabbage keeps well when frozen in airtight containers.

title: sweet pickles(one quart, microwave)
directions: In a small bowl, combine salt, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, vinegar and sugar.
Mix cucumber and onions in microwave-safe bowl.
Pour
vinegar mixture over.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave 5 minutes more.
Stir well.
Cool.
Pour in jar and chill.
Ready to use.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In blender, blend onion and
worcestershire sauce until fine mush.
Add beef cubes, mayo and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth and creamy.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix hamburger, crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Press on cookie sheet to 1/2-inch thick.
Refrigerate overnight, then cut into squares, roll in flour and fry in skillet until light brown.
Put meat in baking pan.
Mix mushroom soup with water.
Pour over meat and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deer sausage gravy
directions: Brown onions, garlic and bell pepper in enough butter to cover bottom of pan.
Add tomato sauce and cook for 30 to 40 minutes. Brown sausage in separate skillet.
When brown, combine both pans and simmer for 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water occasionally if liquid level gets too low.
Serve over rice or potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation Time:
2 hours.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Makes 3 layers.
Alternate biscuits and sugar mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or 375°.

title: simple soy wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place wings in shallow baking dish. In a bowl, mix soy sauce and oil and brush on chicken wings. Bake, uncovered, basting frequently, for 1 hour or until tender.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir through.
Put in large baking dish.
Bake at 400° until bubbling.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until done; drain off grease. Add pork and beans and barbecue sauce.
Heat thoroughly until bubbly hot.

title: apple dandy
directions: Peel, core and thickly slice apples.
Grease 10-inch pan or baking dish.
Pat apples into pan.
Pour syrup over apples.
Mix sugar, flour and rest of ingredients into a crumb topping.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with top-quality vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt.

title: corn meal fried catfish
directions: Rinse catfish fillets; pat dry.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Mix corn meal, flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir in milk, eggs, pepper sauce and 2 tablespoons vegetable oil until well blended.
Heat oil (2 to 3 inches) in Dutch oven to 375°.
Coat fish with corn meal batter, shaking off any excess.
Fry fish in batches for 5 to 8 minutes, or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in a 275° oven.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese, butter, salt and pepper in saucepan. Stir constantly over low heat until cheese melts.
Add corn and blend.
Garnish with chopped fresh parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon-lime jello, cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Mix lemon and lime Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water until dissolved.
Add 2 more cups cold water.
Allow to cool until it starts to set.
Add the softened cream cheese, mixed with 1/4 cup of water and the Ricotta cheese, mixed with 1/4 cup of water. Stir vigorously or use a mixer.
Then stir in the crushed pineapple.
Allow to set in the refrigerator.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix together
cabbage
and onion.
Combine in saucepan, sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed, dry mustard and brown sugar. Heat until it starts
to
boil; stir well.
Pour over cabbage. Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine; blend in flour, add onion. Gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Add chicken, vegetables and salt; heat to bubbling.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole; add pimiento if desired.

title: old fashioned prune butter(low-fat)
directions: In heavy saucepan, put prunes and 3 cups water.
Bring to boil and reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, until prunes are very soft, 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain and return cooked prunes to saucepan; add honey, vinegar, lemon zest, cinnamon and allspice. Simmer gently, stirring and pressing with a wooden spoon to break up the prunes.
Cook until very thick, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
(Can be stored, covered, in refrigerator for 2 weeks or in freezer up to 6 months.)
Excellent on whole wheat bread.
Contains per tablespoon, 41 calories and 0 grams fat.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Grease 3 - 9 inch layer pans.
Mix all ingredients and pour even amount into each pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: strawberry cookies(mazurki)
directions: Combine oleo and flour.
Mix sugar with 2 eggs and beat into oleo mixture.
Spread on ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread preserves on dough. Combine 1 cup sugar with 4 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour over top of preserves and bake at 350° for 30 minutes longer.
When cooled, dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into diamond shapes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind all this through food chopper.
Pour boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Pour boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain, then add last 3 ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes. Seal.

title: grandma's old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, salt and nutmeg.
Add eggs and ice water.
Work in flour.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown around edges. Sprinkle with sugar if desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator 2 hours or more.

title: deep dish chocolate pie(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt; stir in egg yolks.
Add milk. Cook in double boiler until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell and top with meringue.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: uncle carl's award winning chili
directions: Combine in large Dutch oven and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw with tomatoes
directions: Do
ahead:
In	a
large
bowl, make layers of cabbage, green pepper
and onions;
sprinkle 1 cup sugar over top.
In saucepan, combine
mustard,
teaspoons sugar, celery seed, salt,
vinegar and
oil;	mix
well and bring to a full boil, stirring.
Pour over cole slaw mixture.
Refrigerate, covered at least 4 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, oil, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Add flour until dough becomes stiff.
Knead on a floured board for about 5 minutes, then put in a greased bowl to rise for about 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Make rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 400° for about 20 or 25 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix sugar, pineapple juice, ginger ale and Kool-Aid together. Add water and ice cream.
Serve.

title: grandma's applesauce
directions: Peel apples and place in large pan of water.
Add salt or lemon juice to the water to keep apples from turning brown.
Next, place peeled apples in a kettle on low heat and add 1 cup water to pan so apples don't stick.
Cook until apples become good and soft.
Then they are done.

title: grapefruit-mint sorbet
directions: Combine boiling water and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves; let cool.
Add grapefruit juice and mint.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until almost firm.
Spoon mixture into a mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until slushy.
Return mixture to pan and freeze 8 hours.
To serve, let mixture stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: liver and bacon
directions: Wash liver and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown bacon in hot frying pan.
Add onion; cook a few minutes and add liver.
Cook, turning frequently, for about 10 minutes or until done.
Remove browned bacon from frying pan while cooking onion and liver after turning liver once.
Add the bacon when finished cooking.
Serve onion with liver and bacon.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix sugar, mayo, onions, egg, salt and pepper with squash.
Stir in 1/4 stick oleo and cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with crackers, remaining oleo and cheese.

title: cherry topping cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare pudding using one cup of milk.
Let cool. After pudding and cake are cool, prepare icing.
Cream oleo and sugar for 5 minutes, then add cooled pudding and continue beating for 5 more minutes.
When light and fluffy, ice cake.
Top with cherries, then chopped nuts.
Thickened pineapple can be substituted for cherries.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: italian style cauliflower
directions: In small saucepan, heat oil, vinegar, garlic and salt.
Place steamed cauliflower in serving bowl.
Pour hot liquid over and serve.

title: best brownies
directions: Grease a small square cake pan.
In small saucepan over low heat melt the chocolate and margarine.
In medium bowl beat eggs well.
Add sugar.
Stir in chocolate, margarine and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Stir lightly.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Makes 16.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel the sweet potatoes and cut into large chunks.
Cover with warm water and the soda; soak for 10 minutes, then drain.
In saucepan, combine sugar, water, salt and orange slices.
Bring to low boil, then add the raw potatoes and cook until syrup is thick and potatoes are done.
When ready to dish, add 2 or 3 tablespoons butter.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: mississippi dip
directions: Cut top off bread.
Hollow out inside of bread. Save bread and top.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Place inside bread. Place top back on bread and wrap in foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with favorite crackers and bread pieces taken out.

title: peggy's blueberry cake
directions: Blend sugar, flour and shortening together to resemble coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup of mixture for crumbs.
Set egg whites aside. Add remaining ingredients to crumb mixture and mix until smooth. Gently fold in egg whites.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread berries on top and add crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken almond
directions: Saute vegetables lightly in butter.
Combine all ingredients in greased casserole.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese, Parmesan cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover the last few minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and salt to soft peaks in small mixer bowl.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts and chocolate bits; stir with spoon.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased foil covered cookie sheet.
Place in 350° oven, then turn oven off and forget for 3 hours or overnight.
To remove, push up under foil.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add flour, soda and salt. Beat well. Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen.

title: aunt miles italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir sliced zucchini and onion in butter for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and Mozzarella cheese into zucchini mixture.
Separate rolls into triangle.
Place in an ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to make a pie shell.
Spread mustard on crust.
Pour vegetable mixture into pie.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pasta fruit salad
directions: Prepare pasta by directions on box; drain.
Blend yogurt and orange juice in small bowl.
Combine with remaining ingredients into large bowl.
Toss gently to coat.
Chill in refrigerator thoroughly.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream the cheeses, garlic spread and mayonnaise together.
Add drained crab meat and spices and blend.

title: walnut macaroons(diabetic)
directions: Combine oats, sugar replacement, salt, vanilla and liquid shortening in medium bowl.
Stir to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add beaten egg and chopped walnuts and stir to blend thoroughly.
Pack onto greased cookie sheet by small amount of cookie mixture (level teaspoonful).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add apples and mix lightly.
Pour mixture into pie pastry.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and cut vents. Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 50 minutes to 1 hour (until crust is brown and apples are tender).
This pie is delicious so live a little!
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
(Makes a peach punch, not too sweet, and very pretty with foam on top.)

title: refrigerator cookie roll
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add flour mixture gradually, making a very stiff dough.
Roll and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill and slice for baking.
These keep well in refrigerator.
Add nuts, raisins, etc.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with Miracle Whip.
Add to taste the sage, celery seed, dash of sugar, salt and poultry seasoning.

title: devilicious eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Mash yolks and blend in dressing.
Refill whites.
Garnish with parsley, pimento or green pepper, if desired.

title: white sauce for cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, shortening and milk in saucepan and heat until boiling.
Cool slightly and stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating until well blended. Especially good with chocolate cake.

title: k's dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is baked, poke holes in cake surface with a fork.
Spread pineapple and juice over cake while hot.
Let cool.
Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Spread pudding over cake.
Cool in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Serves 12.

title: italian quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
In small bowl, combine crackers, margarine and zucchini.
Press into bottom and sides of pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in yogurt, tomato and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: hearty vegetable chicken soup
directions: First Layer:
1 medium or large head of lettuce

title: kristina's kupcakes(miniature chocolate cheese cupcakes)
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt until smooth, then stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Sift flour, cocoa, sugar and baking soda into a mixing bowl.
Make a well and place in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth with whisk.
Fill miniature muffin pans with chocolate mixture and top with 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: ultimate chicken strips
directions: In a bowl, combine buttermilk, bouillon and oregano. Let stand 1 minute. Stir in chicken and let stand 30 minutes. In plastic bag, combine flour and paprika. Add chicken, a few pieces at a time. Coat, then dip in buttermilk mixture, then with flour again. Fry until golden brown on both sides. Serve with Peach Sauce.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: To Prepare:
Boil spaghetti.
Drain and add oleo, broccoli and chicken. Mix milk, soup and cheese.
Mix together with spaghetti. Serve hot.

title: chocolate coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Roll into small balls, then dip into chocolate and wax which has been melted together.
Place on wax paper to dry.
Store in an airtight container.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Boil together first four ingredients to 238°.
Remove from heat and let stand until cool.
Beat additional cream, a teaspoon at a time, until mixture becomes light in color and a soft consistency to spread on cake.

title: jello shake
directions: Scoop ice cream into blender. Add enough milk to cover ice cream. Pour in 1/2 package of Jell-O. Add a few drops of vanilla flavoring. Blend until smooth and creamy. Pour into frozen mugs and Enjoy!

title: hot snacks
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain grease.
Add spices and mix.
Add cubed cheese and cook slowly until cheese melts.
Place mixture on rye slices, then on cookie sheet.
Freeze until frozen. Place in plastic bag.
Heat at 350° until cheese is bubbly, about 10 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cut smoked sausage into 1/2 to 3/4 inch circles.
Place broccoli flowerets and sausage into a vegetable steamer over boiling water, cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes (until crisp and tender).
Remove from heat and set aside.
Saute onions (not the green onions), mushrooms and bell peppers.	Add the carrot to onion mixture, cover, drain and set aside.
Combine whipping cream, broth, sliced green onions, basil and salt in a medium skillet. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let thicken.
Cook linguine according to package directions - drain and place in a large bowl.
Add reserved vegetables, whipping cream mixture and sliced mushrooms.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and pepper.	Toss and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: popikosh(beef paprika)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, cayenne and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours, adding more water as needed.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Serve over noodles.

title: chocolate drink mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve:
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: coquilles st. jacques
directions: If the large sea scallops are used, cut each into 3 or 4 pieces.
Wash scallops; remove any shell particles and drain.

title: bullseye(a fun way to serve children eggs)
directions: First prepare the bread by cutting a hole in the middle of the slice.
Use a water glass or child's plastic cup.

title: pepper steak(slow cooker)
directions: Cut round steak into strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Toss with steak strips to coat thoroughly.
Add to electric pot along with onions (minced), garlic clove and green pepper (cut in 1/2-inch strips).

title: wassail
directions: Simmer 15 minutes.
A crock-pot is handy for keeping it hot.

title: home-style baked beans
directions: Mix together onion, mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Place baked beans in a baking pan.
Add pancake syrup to baked beans. Slowly stir in mixture of onion, mustard, etc.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple waldorf salad
directions: Mix together.
Cool and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
In casserole dish, pour half of squash mixture, then a layer of cheese slices.
Add the rest of squash mixture and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes. Remove from oven.
Top with more cheese slices and return to oven another 5 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Drain lima beans.
Do not drain other beans.
Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Brown beef and onion in bacon grease, then mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix meat mixture with beans.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Put chicken on to boil with salt, pepper, celery, carrots, onions and parsley flakes.
Boil all of the ingredients for 1 hour or until tender.
(Boil the ingredients in 4 cups water.)
Remove the chicken and add 1 can undiluted soup.
After soup comes to a boil, add noodles and chicken; let cook for 12 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend the sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning together until smooth.
Spread mixture in pan.
Top with toppings.

title: carolina delights
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and milk and boil for one minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, and oatmeal. Stir. Drop onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: apple oatmeal breakfast
directions: Cook oats according to package. Stir in apples, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon. Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples thin.
Put in bottom of pie pan. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon on top. Mix butter, egg, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Put over sliced apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix ingredients; at the end add egg whites.
Mix well.
Put in 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice balls(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Add rice to salted
water;
bring
to
a
boil.
Simmer until rice is mushy.
Remove
from heat; add margarine.
Cool. Fry meat in 1/4 cup
oil until meat loses redness.
Add onions and celery and cook
slowly for 10 minutes.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add
parsley, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside to cool.

title: simple greek shrimp
directions: In an electric skillet, melt the butter over low heat.
Add the green pepper and onion; saute until crisp-tender (about five minutes).
Add the tomatoes and clam broth, the wine and rice. Increase the heat to medium-high and boil for 25 to 30 minutes. Add the shrimp and clams; reduce the heat to medium.
Simmer for three minutes.
Transfer to a serving dish; sprinkle with the Feta cheese.
Enjoy!

title: cold eggplant appetizers(microwave)
directions: Place whole eggplant on microproof baking rack.
Pierce skin in several places.
Cook on High (maximum power) 6 to 7 minutes or until soft.
Set aside to cool.
Combine onion, green pepper, garlic and lemon juice in small microproof bowl.
Cook on High (maximum power) 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until vegetables are limp. Cut eggplant in half; scoop pulp into small mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients except yogurt.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in yogurt, cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Drain.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Then, add drained hamburger mixture and 8 ounces of noodles which have been cooked according to package directions.
Mix everything together and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle top with 3/4 cup cashews the last 10 minutes.

title: mrs. betty's tuna
directions: Mix all these items together and simmer a few minutes.
Don't let it stick.
Serve on biscuits or toast.
Serves about 4 people.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place hen in large pot.
Cook with all seasonings and 3 cups water on high until steaming, on low until tender.
When chicken is done, remove meat and dice into small pieces.
Place chicken in large baking dish.
Brown flour and fat in skillet; add stock and cook until thickened.
Pour over chicken.
When pie dough is ready, pour chicken mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; 350° for 30 minutes more.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices together 3 times. Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and tomato soup alternately in small amounts, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into small greased tube pan or loaf pan and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 24 hours before cutting.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place cut
up chicken in roasting pan.	Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix
creamy Italian dressing and apricot preserves together
and
pour
over
chicken.
Sprinkle
onion soup over mixture.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chinese fried rice with shrimp and egg
directions: In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons salad oil and saute rice until golden brown.
Combine soup mix and water and stir into rice.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. In another skillet heat remaining oil and saute shrimp quickly for about 1 minute.
Add eggs, stirring constantly, and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Stir shrimp and egg mixture into soup-rice mixture, heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve topped with scallions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into pastry shell and bake for 45 minutes.

title: braised pork
directions: Cut pork about 1 1/2-inch cube size.
Wash and dry pork. Place meat in a covered stock-pot.
Add all ingredients except water.
Stir and add water.
Stir.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes to 1 hour and liquid reduced to approximately 1 cup.
Serve over rice.

title: artichoke-rice casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Add artichokes with juice; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: swiss alpine pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Drain broccoli.
Layer half of broccoli, ham and cheese in unbaked pie shell.
Repeat second layer.
Sprinkle top with onion.
Set aside.
Gradually stir milk into beaten eggs; add seasonings.
Pour over mixture in pie shell. Bake 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in container of blender and process 10 seconds.
Stir in coconut; pour into a buttered 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set (pie will puff, then fall slightly).
Cool, chill thoroughly.
Pie makes own crust.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Drain and rinse with cold water. Mix together mayonnaise, salad dressing and dill weed with a whisk. Add pasta and vegetables. Chill.

title: cheese n' vegetable chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Cook celery, carrots and green onion in butter.
Add potato soup, chicken broth, water, parsley and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir until boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in shredded cheese, evaporated milk and sherry. Heat through (do not boil).
Sprinkle with additional sliced green onion.
